{"Author": "Chris M", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "So many useless features. It's really just a novelty unless you can afford to kit out your entire home with Hue or Nest products. The features that are useful, such as playing Spotify, are so basic that it's easier to just use the app on your phone. Better interaction with different dialects is a must."}
{"Author": "Matthew Foulds", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app is almost unusable and never loads. It's a shame because the Alexander is a great product but Amazon hasn't focused on the companion app enough and makes the whole experience frustrating and difficult to use. Please improve support on the app and make it work to make the most of the alexa."}
{"Author": "LaVerne Jones", "Date": "September 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I see Amazon Echo as a device for the next level of intellectual technology. As Amazon expands with other companies to make the Echo usful for talking to more devices. Not everyone can hook up to Alexa yet. This disadvantages those that do have Alexa. I bought the Fire stick believing that Alexa and the stick would talk to my TV like I saw on the Dish Network commercial. Amazon please make Alexa work with all HDTV by developing access or devices without having to by all these pieces. I believe Alexa or any communication device that creates a smart atmosphere is the future. I can see this technology, as it it develops, being present everywhere even in automobile."}
{"Author": "Patrick Day", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I use an LG V10 and its a pretty good phone. That said, the app does nothing! No scores, no news, I can't ask it about the weather. I love Amazon but c'mon guys you can at least make this work on my V10 which runs Nougat."}
{"Author": "Leonie Jeffries", "Date": "September 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can you do calls/text using this? I don't have the speech bubble in the middle on home page to start this? Also I want to easily connect to the TV so Alexa can change channels and play Netflix on my TV. When is this going to become available?"}
{"Author": "David Hildebrand", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App works in premise, but needs a lot of work. The option to adjust the volume is not to my liking, it's very cumbersome and I have to make several adjustments to get it right. Don't even get me started on Alexa not understanding basic commands."}
{"Author": "David Messenger", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I like using Alexa but I really want to use the list function more effectively. I don't understand why we don't have the option to have more than one list. Could it be that Amazon fears we might buy something from somewhere else besides Amazon?  Also, the list does not put enough items on a page (too much whitespace).  Deleting items should be done by checking boxes and then clicking a single delete button.  Why do we have to click each item two times?"}
{"Author": "Nishant Sinha", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Well it doesn't look like a native app and seems it runs a website beneath and is slow. The echo device is great once setup. But the setup process is too painful and annoying. During setup at times it just doesn't recognize wifi networks. If I change my wifi passpord, running the whole setup is too difficult. The app ( or rather the website undeneath app ) also gets unresponsive sometimes in few setup screens, specially after the app connects to echo and it shows a 'Continue' button which doesn't respond. EDIT: I got a new echo Dot and setup is hung up on step showing 'Attempting to connect to echo dot'. The phone got connected to the dots WiFi but nothing happens in setup process. Setup is just too painful."}
{"Author": "Joe H", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Pretty helpful as far as apps go. Couple of things need to happen though. Needs a volume widget option. I cant seem to find one. More importantly the list function needs help i shoild be able to make multiple shopping lists for things. Grocery car household ect. Should be able customize that. In addition i should be able to tell it to add a group of things and have them show up as individual items. So i need eggs cheese bred milk. All in one sentence finally i want it to automatically group things at least by hot and cold items but even better if it could recognize delli meat produce ect.  Do that and 5 stars all day. Needs a little work yet on voice recognition but pretty good."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Use my 3 Echo's daily. New app version definitely slower. Should allow basic phone dialing without having to put my phone number in cloud. Privacy issue. No one's busy if I have Alexa or not. Should be user configurable."}
{"Author": "Robert Kochman", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Terrible! Keeps telling me it's offline even though I'm connected. Slow! Shopping List is erratic. I have a Show, Dot, and two Echos and love them. Why is this app so bad?!"}
