{"Author": "Andy Clapham", "Date": "September 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Doesn't seem to actually be Alexa. Was expecting to be able to voice search and control, however I get the option to \"just use the Alexa app\" and nothing happens when I click on it. Disappointing."}
{"Author": "Brian Dunigan", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is the most unintuitive app I've ever used. For example: why are there multiroom music settings under smart home? And why is the multi room music feature so difficult to use. Like I should be able to switch to multi room or single room while playing from the app. Also why do groups show up as devices of their own if you can't do anything with them from the app.  Like terrible design all around"}
{"Author": "Phil Craig", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I had no problems with the app, but as new features are introduced to Alexa, the app hasn't improved alongside. The grouping setting does not work at all. As soon as I try to give a name to the group, the app crashes out. Have reported fault with no response or fix."}
