{"Author": "Rishi Sachdeo", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App was ok before, not the best but was working at least. Since update to Oreo it force closes when I try to modify alarms. The Oreo developer window started a while ago, I have a hard time understanding how Amazon didn't check to make sure basic functions work in the new environment. How did this not get tested or even detected during basic debugging? I'll update my review when you update the App you require customers to use for the device they bought from you."}
