{"Author": "Rob Williams", "Date": "October 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Dear Amazon, I liked the app when it worked. Now it doesn't work. I don't like things that don't work especially if I've paid for something that is supposed to work. The app now doesn't even show info when loaded despite being reinstalled several times it just shows the home button and the other button at the bottom of the screen, everything else is blank. Google are giving away a free Google home with the release of the pixel 2 at the end of the month. It would be a shame to lose customers because your app doesn't work..."}
{"Author": "Megan Goodwin", "Date": "October 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Just found out this app ran 5GB of my data in the background. I got a text from my provider saying \"I used all of my High Speed data for the month\" but I'm only 4 days into the plan for this month. I've never used that much data that fast! I check my data usage in my setting and this app was listed at the top with 5.4GB used, and 5GB of that ran in the background!?! I recently updated that app so I don't know if that's what caused it to do that, but it's only used at most 25MB in previous months."}
{"Author": "simon walker", "Date": "August 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Finally after many frustrating months decided to delete to save space. The thing is a trial of little real value. If you want, for example,accurate info on traffic etc use ok Google and also streaming from local storage. Luckily the dot was a present so not out of pocket. Wishing others more luck."}
{"Author": "Chris Mc", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app is appalling. How can the app for such a good voice assistant be so slow and buggy? The app is literally unusable 90% of the time."}
{"Author": "Mark Davis", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app is quite bad. It's unconscionably slow. Initial load times are slow. Opening the now playing is slow. Everything takes ages, are we sure it's 2017 and I'm on a high end device?  Additionally, functionality is not what it should be. Why is playing Amazon's own music service so hard? Sometimes Alexa doesn't understand me and I want to play a specific song or album from Amazon Music Unlimited - you can't, apparently it's just radio and popular. What on Earth and I paying for this service for then? Spotify gives you full control of Alexa music from the app.   Also while the new whole home audio festure is welcome, it's still lacking. I need to be able to submit a device into multiple groups. I have five echos. Maybe I want a group for my upstairs echos, my downstairs echos, and a whole home option? Can't do that. Silly."}
{"Author": "Cash Simpson", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Used to be amazing but had really come to junk. Every time i go to my settings it just loads forever! So annoyed! You'd think with growing pressure from Google Home and others that Amazon would step up their game. Time to try the competition."}
{"Author": "Brent Hoard", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Crashes when making groups for multi room music. Seriously, did you test it? Amazon marketing is busy sending out emails about this \"great new feature\" but the devs dropped the ball. Did the interns do this commit and build?"}
{"Author": "Gregg LaPore", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Wow, this app has really gone downhill. A full 90 seconds to sync to my Dot? No volume control? \"Your Dot is disconnected\" while it's playing music..... really? Really? Great product. Embarrassingly bad app."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I rate all apps with useless changelogs 1 star. Want a better rating? Put what you change in the changelogs."}
{"Author": "Annoy Droid", "Date": "August 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The feedback option is grayed out so how do you give feedback? I've had it for a few days and the novelty is wearing off."}
{"Author": "Todd Sackett", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Needs to support multiple Spotify accounts (a different account per dot). Is super slow, and just stops working often."}
{"Author": "Cliff Brown", "Date": "August 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Buggy, slow and sadly a requirement if you own an Echo. Hopefully Amazon will spend some time on actually fixing this app. It is bad on all platforms."}
{"Author": "Laura Jones", "Date": "August 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My Alexa has not worked since the app updated. The app is useless on my S7. I can't set alarms or anything on it. I use to love my Alexa... not anymore. She has quit working."}
{"Author": "Jeff Ballard", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "One star because the app crashes whenever a drop-down is selected. Nexus 6p, running Oreo, can't even contact support in the app because it uses drop-downs and causes there crash.  One that is fixed, it's a four star app for controlling your Echo's"}
{"Author": "Jonathan Liechti", "Date": "September 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Since the last few updates it constantly freezes. Can turn alarms on and off without it freezing and crashing when you pick and alarm time.  9/9/17- wow it's sad that am app revolving around the Amazon echo system is this buggy. You still cannot select and edit alarms without it freezing constantly. This happens on my brand new iPad as well as my year old android phone. App constantly crashes. Very poorly designed app."}
{"Author": "Kat Cole", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worked fine in the beginning. Now I can't even open the app. It says there is a certificate error and I need to update Chrome. My Chrome is already updated, so not sure what it needs."}
{"Author": "Teagan Mustain", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I bought the alexa before the calling feature. Now it will not let me update the app without enabling that feature. That is Insane!!! I unistalled and gave the damn thing away."}
{"Author": "Mike Watson", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Tried to give my echo to my boss and app is poorly made. basically useless. Had hard time reconnecting echo back to my device. App needs to be redone. Shouldn't have to be this difficult to connect a device. How can you lure new customers if it's hard to connect device when it should be easy."}
{"Author": "David D", "Date": "August 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not great to be honest. Struggles to recognise voice often and repeats something absolutely different that sounds in no way similar to what you say. It will also start speaking randomly when not being used. Usually at least 10 second delay between request being confirmed and the song/radio station coming on. Wish I'd bought Google device instead."}
{"Author": "John Schaenzer", "Date": "August 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app has a full page pop up for message and voice calling. Unless you give it access to this it will not go away and you cannot do anything else. This makes the app useless."}
{"Author": "NJ E", "Date": "August 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Kind of a mess, like a 3rd grader designed it. e.g. All Skills. One would think this is where all my Echo's skills are. Then the link to them is pretty undiscoverable. Why not rename All Skills \"Skills Store\" and Your Skills as a separate menu item. Or just redesign the entire app."}
{"Author": "Brian P", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Cant send messages or make calls from contacts. If you want echo to do that then the people your contacting have to have this app too. Cant get it to record messages like on the commercials either. App is quite useless."}
{"Author": "Damon Beaven", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I love my Alexa. I hate this app. It crashes too much and it just uses confusing verbiage. Trying to enable multiple room music... And it crashes when I try to name the group."}
{"Author": "Heidi Pie", "Date": "August 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I love amazon and expected good things but Alexa is really disappointing. She can barely answer any questions OK Google is so much better! When I don't want to speak to Alexa because someone is sleeping but I want to put some quiet music on there's no search function for Amazon unlimited music WTF!??? There's an AtoZ of like thousands of artists that takes ages to loads and god forbid you want to listen to an artist beginning with Z. You might be the a year trying to find it!! Plough some of those dodged tax \u00a3\u00a3\u00a3 into giving us a better experience please!"}
{"Author": "Rajesh Dubal", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not bad, not great. Limited functionality. Can't listen to my Audible ebooks on the Echo. Very bland interface. Could be so much more. Customer services is the worst I've ever experienced. Save yourself a couple of hours of your life and don't ring them for help."}
{"Author": "Oliver Grange", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Since downloading the current update, I have lost all control and updating of my device info via the app. It has ruined my dot which was very useful before. Come on Amazon, pull your finger out, people are investing good money in to your products which are now far less useful!"}
{"Author": "SK SW", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Unbelievably useless. Can't check things as simple as tide times or local traffic. In order to check traffic you have to set as a commute, hardly time saving I can use maps for that! Hopefully it'll improve. I'll check back in a year or so......"}
{"Author": "Monica Hui", "Date": "August 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App has updated and wants me to join the friend/family call/message system. Don't need unwanted calls or messages on Alexa especially since once it is set up, you can't turn it off or block anyone."}
{"Author": "Imogen S", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Edit: Since the last update, I haven't been able to send any feedback. It works OK once it actually decides to load. Or I should say, it basically works. Little things often seem to be breaking, like if something set your Echo off, you might want to know what, but often it won't register that I've clicked play on a voice clip. So yeah, mostly works except when it doesn't."}
{"Author": "Andrew Goldstein", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Slow and clunky.  Poor search capabilities in Prime Music Unlimited.  Does many things, but sort of a hot-mess in UI and ease of accomplishing task.  Please keep working on it, Amazon, and focus on speed and simplicity."}
{"Author": "Roddy Neff", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Needs to be updated. When video calling in the echo show, the audio is routed through the ear piece instead of the speakerphone. Not very convenient when you have to hold it in front of your face."}
Amazon Alexa: Number of reviews: 353
"Insteon for Hub"
{"Author": "John Fitzgerald", "Date": "October 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Android app has nice layout but also has a bug, when programming the dual outlet into a scene, the bottom outlet refuses to respond to the off command, if programmed with an ios device,  the outlet responds correctly. Insteon support said they would call me back on this issue, its been 4 days and i am still waiting. The insteon line overall is a great and affordable way to automate your lighting system. It has been rock solid, easy to install and a great value for the money. Fix the android bug and it will get 5 stars from me."}
{"Author": "Michael Adelman", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app works but has limitations.  On level is not configurable, no matter what the setting is the switch comes on to full level. Would be nice to be able to add custom icons. App freezes every once in a while. The interface is as basic as can be. It constantly runs in the background, draining the battery."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app functions correctly but is slow to load and login, there are no widgets or hot keys, and interaction with nest thermostat is spotty. It needs a makeover badly. If I didn't already invest in insteon hardware I'd use others Update: many updates later and reliability of hub/app is not improved. You need a home controller to do anything serious. I can't believe I'm saying this considering my early adoption, but avoid Insteon."}
{"Author": "Derek Weber", "Date": "October 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Extremely outdated. Needs a major overhaul. Hard to use and not yet friendly. Scene schedules don't seem to be working yet they are all set up correctly and turn on/off if you do it manually. If I didn't already have money invested in this hardware I'd be getting something else that works better."}
{"Author": "KNGPIN GANGSTA", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app without a doubt sucks! I've had insteon products since 08 my entire home is outfitted with switches and lamplinks. 15 light switched are duds and the remaining lamp links are on their way out. This app constantly crashes. I've submitted complains to smarthome and they claim to have someone on the case. This was 3 months ago. I'm going to find another product to invest in that is more reliable that this garbage! You pay premium\u200b price for a sub par product. I'm done with you insteon!"}
{"Author": "Davor Balzar", "Date": "September 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is really weird. Just got new Note8 and it doesn't want to connect to the hub. It worked with Galaxy S8 and still works fine through Alexa, which means that it's about disliking Note8. Any ideas, please?"}
{"Author": "Adam Sperber", "Date": "October 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Horribly designed app. Non-intuitive, when is Insteon going to listen and build a NEW app?????? Hello? Is anyone there?"}
{"Author": "Joe Webb", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This App sucks!!!!!   Says it can't connect to my \"HUB\" but shows it found my WI FI with no further options but to start over with the same \"DEAD END\" results.  I regret ever buying a device that evidently is outdated and no one ever tried the APP with their device."}
{"Author": "Mark Augustine", "Date": "October 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Has been very finicky booting since recent update. Keeps going back to the login screen or sometimes screen just goes black."}
{"Author": "logmeindog", "Date": "October 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "With latest update, app no longer opens. Just pops up then closes, pops up then closes. Worthless!! -galaxy S8"}
{"Author": "Madhu Chandrakumar", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Due for a much needed update to UI and overall performance.  Significantly drains the battery because of the poorly optimized app."}
{"Author": "Tom Lastname", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Waaaaaay outdated design. In a serious need for an overhaul."}
{"Author": "Victor Medina", "Date": "September 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's ok does the job"}
{"Author": "David Setton", "Date": "July 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The entire app needs to be overhauled with more android specific functionality.  The use of widgets would be a huge help as some of the other reviews mention.  Also, some tasks could easily be reduced to 1 step instead of 2.  God knows why they have a switch icon that doesn't give the ability to dim and brighten the light right away (only on and off).  This should be the first thing that is addressed."}
{"Author": "Andrew Rossignol", "Date": "July 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The UI is outdated. They finally fixed connectivity issues when switching between networks that I reported months ago. I am moving soon and will probably switch automation systems rather than buying more insteon modules unless this app gets more attention."}
{"Author": "J H", "Date": "August 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have been using this app for 3 years.  It has not changed and it is totally outdated now. It constantly has trouble connecting. If I did not have 10 devices on insteon I would have changed systems by now. Every other monitoring app allows the screen to enlarge the camera. Are you ever going to update this app?"}
{"Author": "Ashley Stevens", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Device maintenance on my Samsung S7 says that this is a battery-wasting app and it seems that's the case. So don't leave this app in the background when not using it as it will drain your battery. Otherwise, it is what it is, it's very limited but seems to work for me. I also have SmartThings and apart from hardware-based Insteon linking (with the buttons on the switches) I do all automation within SmartThings. There's groovy code out there for the SmartThings IDE to integrate Insteon switches and dimmers which is all I use, mainly for the Keylinc keypads which no other manufacturer has."}
{"Author": "Don LeGower", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Totally looses time if power goes off.  Should synchronize to the internet, it has ethernet! can't deal with daylight savings change,  app doesnt display hub time, so to reset the hub time you have to sign in with a computer. The only updates they make are to sell new products.  overall rates just about zero. If it can't keep time, it's useless. The fact that it can't display it's time is also just ridiculous....."}
{"Author": "Anthony Lombardo", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I'm terribly disappointed in this app. I recognize the source code also. A lot of people are using it. It has very limited capabilities in my opinion. Ive seen free apps that do better if they would only get rid of those intrusive ads. The Camera portion is just completely useless. All you can do with it basically is look to see whats there. none of the other functions work well at all. And I just found out they are no longer supporting it and I just bought one last week. ERR"}
{"Author": "Ryan Unash", "Date": "August 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App successfully authenticates but never connects to the hub on my nexus 6p but works fine on my fianc\u00e9s nexus 5x. Waited months for support to fix it but they have been no help. Horrible app and service"}
{"Author": "Chris Beran", "Date": "July 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Terrible connectivity, apparently only connects to the phones it wants to. Have the exact same pbone as my father, it works on his, not on mine. I've found better quality in a kids meal toy."}
{"Author": "Brad J", "Date": "August 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Just realized that all of my Motion Sensors and Open/Close sensors are no longer sending notifications or show a status even though the scenes are working fine. (lights turn on and off when walking by a MS) Swapped out batteries but no change. When I check the  Plug In Modules and I/O Link modules they all show correct status changes and can be controlled by the app. I removed and re-added my OC sensors and they started statusing and send push notifications again. Bummer - this means I have to spend a couple of hours reprogramming all my Motion Sensors and scenes. The hardware is great but the App has long been a thorn. Have several out buildings so need the power band and relay feature. Got 3 of these hubs at three sites but last year I stopped buying Insteon and have been purchasing"}
{"Author": "Dru Yoder", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The ui is in need of a huge update and the application always has issues connecting.  Most of the time the app opens and then shuts down all on its own."}
{"Author": "Sal Battaglia", "Date": "July 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Waste of Money. Do not buy Insteon products. Update made all of my devices unknown and I need to factory reset all of them. I have 20 devices. Not acceptable."}
{"Author": "Bill Doerfler", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It works, just slow and plodding. Feels like an app from 5 it 6 years ago. Can be a bit of a pain to use on occasion, and I can't tell if that is because I'm off my home network not."}
{"Author": "Douglas York II", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Adding a new device is not intuitive.  Neither is changing it's settings.  Not happy an Internet connection is required for scheduling.  IMO the events should be saved in the hub."}
{"Author": "Chad Shumway", "Date": "July 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Hard to believe this is the 21st century.  This app is very lackluster for a total home control system. At least the apple version auto rotates."}
{"Author": "William Kutzler", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "You can't control anything until you manually poll the config from the hub, otherwise it'll loop back every time you try to control a device. Every time you open the app it should poll the hub."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The image does not auto-rotate to full screen when turning phone on its side.  Please incorporate this feature Please!  Otherwise works well for the money."}
{"Author": "Anner J. bonilla", "Date": "July 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Cannot find the stupid hub even if it's on the network and the debug menu is accessible from my web browser."}
{"Author": "Brandon Bey", "Date": "July 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Make other keypad buttons work in stringify please. Main on and off is not enough."}
{"Author": "Josh Brewer", "Date": "August 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works great with my Galaxy s8. One bug I noticed is that the light on/off toggle does not work when power saving is on, which isn't crutial for me."}
{"Author": "Justin Cramer", "Date": "July 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Major improvement in app load speed. It's nearly tolerable as a useful application now."}
{"Author": "Jennifer Lewis", "Date": "July 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Drains my battery."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "July 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Camera came with no instructions  I hate it"}
{"Author": "Erick Perez", "Date": "June 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "As soon as I leave and my phone switches over to LTE, the app pops up saying it lost its connection to my hub. Highly annoying.    As far as the rest of the app, it works and that's about it. App hasn't changed much since it's debut and it shows. UI is extremely outdated and several old bugs remain unfixed. Insteon as a whole is behind the curve on home automation despite being one of the oldest companies in the game.  I'm ditching Insteon as soon as I can."}
{"Author": "John G", "Date": "May 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I've never been able to connect to the hub during initial set-up for the last 3 months. I bought this product from Costco brand new and have never been able to use it. Very bad product. Not user friendly. Read all the other reviews. I'm not alone on this. Stay away! Don't waste your money."}
{"Author": "John Robb", "Date": "July 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Insteon was a great idea.   I've invested over $1500 in equipping my house with Insteon devices and now I'm regretting it.  The android app is not keeping pace with eh iOS app.    I had to upgrade my hub to get access to my Logitech Harmony remotes.  I still can't access my Sonos devices even though this is a feature found on the iOS version for over a year.    Yes the app turns on my lights but that's about all I can use it for."}
{"Author": "Rob Mastronicola", "Date": "May 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I am so fed up with this app. If I didn't have so much money invested I would never use insteon again. Horrendous interface. GET OUT WHILE YOU CAN. Been a user for 3 years and have not seen any huge improvements to functionality or usability. Wish they focused on Android as much as they do iOS."}
{"Author": "Alan henson", "Date": "March 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Why do I have to restart and put in my password everyone I open this app. It's terrible. I love my insteon products by this app makes me want to buy another brand and switch them all out. Insteon you are seriously hurting your product with this app. You're lucky Alexa came along."}
{"Author": "Douglas Blaikie", "Date": "May 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not working... AGAIN.... new update pushed out to app a couple of days ago. Today hub decides it doesn't want to talk to anything..... Whole house is configured with insteon. So when it doesn't work the word \"frustrating\" just doesn't cut it."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "July 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I've had the Insteon system for 4 plus years in two separate homes and it has worked flawlessly from the start.  I suspect that most users with problems don't really know how to set up or use the system.  I have about 12 devices connected including cameras, all work well all the time."}
{"Author": "Tim M.", "Date": "June 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "When the user brings up the app a second time, it has lost contact with the devices and cannot regain. The user must then press the back button a couple of times I'm so the system can log itself in again at which point it will properly determine the status of each device and allow the user to control them again. In contrast my alarm app and garage door controller app are always ready to go with the proper status whenever opened! So there's no reason insteon can't be as reliable. Otherwise their products themselves get four or five stars from me! Just not the stupid app."}
{"Author": "Kurt Sanger", "Date": "May 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Still does not see keypads.  Even after updating app and hub.  Updating hub requires manually recording, deleting, and reinstalling every device.   Otherwise it's great.  But I wanted to program 4 button keypad to control a scene and you may not."}
{"Author": "George Karayiannis", "Date": "March 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app does not allow you to customize or move the order of icons for Devices/Rooms/Scenes. They are placed automatically in Alphabetical order and that it. You have to live with it!! Also, one of the most annoying things is that for the 6 or 8 key dimmer switches, it doesn't come up as how it looks. It comes up as a basic switch, and then you have to click on the \"+\" every time, in order to expand it to view the whole keypad. Ridiculous! This should have been an option in the settings to choose default. By the way, if your hub doesn't have Internet, it is impossible to connect through your phone over Wifi to set anything up. The hub ALWAY needs to be able to reach the cloud, otherwise consider this whole system a paperweight."}
{"Author": "Andrey Chepurnoy", "Date": "June 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Super basic UI, especially compared to the iOS version. Issue with connection being lost if the app idles in the background for longer than 10 minutes. The app will open and devices will sit there attempting to update their status forever. App must then be force quit and restarted. This was reported to Insteon in January 2017 and has not been address as of this writing in June 2017. The problem is reproduced on both my Android phones."}
{"Author": "777 Equanimity", "Date": "May 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Money for hub, money for cameras and a big waste of time. First hub went out now second one fails to connect. Reset everything and still nothing. I am totally fed up with this app and brand. Tells you to update app, but when you go to app there is no update available. If not resolved soon, will be going to something else!"}
{"Author": "Jonathan Baker", "Date": "July 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Has serious issues. Will not reauthenticate if opened from a suspended state, leaving no way to control lights. Nothing like messing with my phone just so I can see my stairs. Very poorly coded."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "April 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Why did i just pay $90 for the hub and have issues with this?? I think this is scammish because you woo people in to buy hub and camera doesnt function like before either SMDH. wtf Look at NEST CAM APP. 4 STARS PLUS ALL THEIR PRODUCTS WORKS IN ONE APP"}
{"Author": "Bruno Silvino", "Date": "February 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Does what it is supposed to do. How come no android wear support yet? I don't understand why I cannot set the public IP address manually. My Hub is getting the wrong IP and I can't access remotely. Very disappointed."}
{"Author": "Richard H.", "Date": "June 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Possibly the worst app ever made. Unreliable and you have to back out of it any time your screen locks. By the time this app connects to the hub, you could have gotten up and turned on the light. Worthless. Let a third party make alternate apps for your system since you are inept."}
{"Author": "Ricardo Palhano", "Date": "May 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Causes orphaned scenes and broken links between devices, when it gets stuck half way creating links, which happens frequently.  Have to force close multiple times throughout day to get status."}
{"Author": "Andy Miller", "Date": "April 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Every time I want to use this app, I have to kill it in my app manager and relaunch it. Otherwise it hangs indefinitely trying to reload the current hub state."}
{"Author": "David LaRocque", "Date": "May 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App won't stop notifications when I set it not to in Android's notification settings. The visuals stop, but the sounds keep coming. It's really annoying when a bunch are queued up, then all come beeping on in."}
{"Author": "Andrew Bates", "Date": "July 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The workflow is frustrating and the pairing is problematic. I had to use an iOS device to add the dimming ballast (2475DA2) as it would not complete using the Android app."}
