{"Author": "", "Date": "November 22, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": " support your lock controllers?</span> When adding a lock controller it display as an on/off switch. And then it never unlocks the door, only locks. Works fine when pressing the button on the lock controller but I can't do that if I'm locked outside the house!"}
{"Author": "John Terwiel", "Date": "October 23, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "</span> Constantly doesn't work. I have to reset Internet modem and hub and phone and sometimes that doesn't even work. Then its turn everything off manually. Pain in the butt."}
{"Author": "Athol Cohen", "Date": "August 26, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App crashes constantly</span> Quite stable on OnePlus Two running Oxygen but the time if still an ongoing issue.  If I set the time on my iPad it's correct but about 20 minutes off on the Android app."}
{"Author": "Leo P", "Date": "August 26, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": " but does not share scenes</span> Whe you setup a dimmer on your phone it also shows up on your tablet.  Not so for scenes.  You have to set those up on each device separately."}
{"Author": "Doug Vinie", "Date": "August 27, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "iew and size</span> Size of camera view is stuck in 1982.  On a note 3 which has a big screen.  Open up my insteon app and camera view only works in portait mode and only fills 30 percent of screen.  Why not allow full screen portrait or landacape. Never seen anything like it."}
{"Author": "Jonathan Iavarone", "Date": "September 2, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "wear</span> Camera does not load AT ALL. This is getting old really. This needs to be updated AND support android wear!!! Its ridiculous that it still doesn't."}
{"Author": "Jason Dessenberg", "Date": "November 18, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "oorly Conceived</span> I don't have any connection problem or least nothing more than normal.  My issue is with the layout.  Why are iphone and Android apps so different?  The layout of the iPhone could be better but it is a whole lot better than the Android app.  I agree, the app needs a redesign.  Make the app across different devices the same."}
{"Author": "Dalbir Taggar", "Date": "October 15, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "pdate 1.9.2</span> Camera screen does not support pan tilt action. Earlier it had four arrows now its missing. No touch action works."}
{"Author": "Joe Prebish", "Date": "November 27, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "stem</span> Easy and Simple home control. Need better and more attentive help."}
{"Author": "Tamara Smith", "Date": "October 28, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "use</span> We have the hub, 2 light plug in's 2 hard wire light switch ' s and a thermostat.   We love our Insteon home."}
{"Author": "Thomas Roach", "Date": "September 23, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can I give 6 stars? Not the greatest (and the equipment is far from the priciest), but they keep working at improving the performance and features. Since this is not a stand-alone app but an operating interface for a home automation controller, I applaud their enthusiasm and dedication."}
{"Author": "Reverend Keseki", "Date": "August 22, 2016", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "let Support Finally here!</span> Dual Outlet Support was seriously the main thing I wanted and now I have it. Thanks Insteon, I just hope you don't continue to put Android on the back burner."}
