{"Author": "Mike Koshzow", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Terrible touch response when using on Galaxy s8 plus. The app was fine on my Nexus 6p, but does not seem to be optimized for the new line of Samsung phones - truly disappointing!"}
{"Author": "Michael Sepulveda", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "You need to fix your servers. They are extremely laggy and take a long time to load videos no matter what connection I am on. The app used to work okay and now for some reason everything takes a long time to load. I have tried it on multiple internet connections and it is for sure the app that is not working properly. Will change my rating once it is fixed thank you."}
{"Author": "Kristina Huynh", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Spins on a black screen instead of the video view for MINUTES when on wifi and strong 4g.  Worthless as a security system as it fails at real time streaming."}
{"Author": "James Prophet", "Date": "October 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Umm.. pausing video is a necessity. I know it used to be there\u200b in-between the back and forward buttons (or just tapping the screen) it's not there now. Also, when saving clips, the clips do not include the original time stamps, which is kinda really important. Someone attempted to gain entry to my house and the video clip I was trying to send to the police had absolutely no date/time or any context. It makes things REALLY confusing and near impossible to determine the order of things when you are comparing video clips between 2 different cameras. Come on guys. Also the app is really laggy when clicking on an \"event\" in portrait mode then switching to landscape, the video cuts out and you miss the event. Also since last update when I slide my finger along the video theres no time lapse. We all spend sooo much monthly for these little features that aren't little the are necessary.  Update: Reinstalled the app, which fixed the issue with time lapse. The rest of my issues remain. Update 2: Time lapse randomly stopped working again."}
{"Author": "Matthew Dauner", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Clean UI, but lacks configuration options for viewing nest cams.  I'm one of many people using multiple cams as a baby monitors. Spaces view is ok but needs features like: 1. No screen time out (only possible when viewing a single camera) 2. Multi-cam audio - this should be simple, just mix the audio from all, raising the volume on individual cams when new noises are heard.  Add in more features and I'll rate it higher."}
