{"Author": "", "Date": "September 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Amazing.."}
{"Author": "Sam Bartle", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Nest was a great idea, and I do like my smart thermostat, but in the UK at least hive is a better choice. It costs less but has much more smart accessories that work with it like bulbs etc.. nest has basically zero. I expected to see nest become a proper Google product and integrate with everything Google but it just hasn't happened. Basically it's not been updated with new features in the last 2 years!!"}
{"Author": "Martin Johnson", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My schedules keep changing automatically. Extra numbers for temperatures keep appearing on my heating schedule, I keep deleting them but they reappear. No response from Nest???  Still not fixed after about 8 months, various updates but the application still has bugs, pull your finger out Google."}
{"Author": "Fisher Jim", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have nest cam, nest protect, and nest thermostat. The nest cam, which after the trial period they want an unacceptable monthly fee to store your alerts, became totally unreliable, the latest update made it worse. Sometimes it turns on when you are out sometimes it doesn't. When it does work, sometimes it gives alerts, sometimes it gives false alerts, sometimes it gives no alerts. Basically a totally expensive let down!"}
{"Author": "Vincent Petersen", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "For the love of Christmas please get rid of the Nest Aware reminder banner at the top of the viewing window, it pops up every few seconds.  It's driving me crazy!    Update: 2/21 OMG these double notifications are driving me crazy, please let us choose a notification sound too, this should be a no brainer.  Update 9/14/17 How do any of the Nest engineers still have jobs? Double notification is back and it's more annoying than ever.  This is making me wanna get rid of Nest all together! It's not reliable and the app is terrible.  This is pathetic."}
{"Author": "Paul Lemay", "Date": "September 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Using a Samsung Galaxy S8. I have to press icons in the app multiple times to get them to work. Tried uninstalling and reinstalling the app. Same problem. When I logged back on the app listed my phone twice for using the home/away feature. Which one am I supposed to select?"}
{"Author": "Thomas Coupe", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App was working fine until recently, the video scrubbing is a bit clunky to find when activity has been noticed in a zone, but it was manageable.   The current issue that's been persisting for a few days now, is duplicate notifications occurring throughout the day for the same activity.   I've reinstalled the app twice and all that succeeded in doing was giving me triple notifications instead of double. More than a bit annoying, so hopefully get fixed soon."}
{"Author": "James Smith", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I  now for some reason get double notifications for every little thing the camera sees!awesome when it goes off in the middle of the night so then MY phone goes off twice,  and my WIFE'S phone goes off twice!  And it no longer can distinguish people from regular motion,  which is one of the reasons i bought this camera in the first place! Please fix!"}
{"Author": "Glenn Lowe", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "With newest update. Notifications ping and vibrate twice for each event. Once for the initial event and again about 2 seconds later when the quick view of the footage loads in the notification tray. With 6 Cameras and the amount of false triggers I get from vehicles driving by, my phone is blowing up. Can't uninstall because I need it, but now I have to silence my phone and I miss important things."}
{"Author": "John Morgado", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "When notifications work its delayed by at least five to 8 minutes if at all. Lately getting double notifications, on 2 outdoor cameras. What's the use of have the Nestaware service if I get a notification 10 minutes latter that a person is at the door. Really disappointed with Nest not addressing these issues, Yes you do have excellent listener's great if you're lonely and need some company. Get a proper forum so user's can help fix and share their issues."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app is helpful but I have called customer service about the lack of ability to tell the thermostat whether I'm Home or Away. I work five miles from home and it always says that I am home. So I have to manually set it. Even then it might chafe because I am using mobile data, not a hot spot. After I change it, it always changes fro Away to Home."}
{"Author": "Thomas McCarthy", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "In regards to the indoor nest cam... The 15sec rewind/forward is kind a garbage. Going back and forth to watch what was previously recorded in general is not great. All n all though... I love the nest cam. It does a good job recording moments of sound and movement. There's a lag in notifying me to when it happens..So, if I get a notification I know that it's not real time... But it's pretty close. I really like the control my wife and I have and i love the quality of video...Which is why I bought it in the 1st place."}
{"Author": "Nick", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "feedback: would like a Nest Car Cam with LTE support, lots of crazy drivers now would like to record cars behavior in front of me.  Since high resolution can take up to 300GB, this might have to wait to 5G :(  -Nest Aware for Nest Cam outdoor need to be smarter, need to be able to profile faces of everyone and have an option to click on a face and show all the clips that face was recorded, and an ability to notify when a new face is detected"}
{"Author": "Jason Langley", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Double notifications are very frustrating.  I turned on notifications for my nest cam a while back and I love getting notified when something happens at the house.  Recently something happened with an update that causes me to get notified twice for everything."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not registering touch input a majority of the time for the icon to change from heat to cool to off. I usually have to spam it and hopefully I get lucky. Using an s8, didn't have this problem with my last phone which was a pixel."}
{"Author": "paul avery", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I am having constant issues with home/away assist not working or working in reverse. Always having to manually turn it on when out. I have 2 Phones linked to the account, one is an S8 the other an S6 and both are on android 7.0 I see lots of other reviews on here with similar problems.  I have reset phones/uninstalled app/uninstalled camera/put it all back on again, worked for 24 hours then back to thinking I'm at home when we are both out.  This is not great security really . Why will you not fix this, I take it you do have App engineers working for you."}
{"Author": "Martin O'Donnell", "Date": "September 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Ok app for Protect but very laggy for Cam Outdoor using timeline,  no timeline in landscape mode,  would like to be able to swipe left/right to skip x amount of time,  this limits to increments of 15secs by pressing,  and why can't we pause the stream? Also would like to have a custom notification sound. Bluetooth not always closing when shutting app now."}
{"Author": "Rev", "Date": "September 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Latest update killed location services completely for my phone. Home/Away doesn't work anymore at all. Even tried factor resetting  phone. Location works perfectly fine with other apps on this phone. Using a Nexus 6P with Android 8.0"}
{"Author": "Kenneth Marsh", "Date": "September 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I'm not sure what happened the last update but it used to work great. My camera message came in and even showed me two sec of vid and when you scroll to your vid it played. Now nope. It just keeps showing a loading sign and sits there. It makes me upset I wish I could go back to the last update. O well I guess. Also the camera drops out for no reason. Over all it's a good camera but the app needs to be fixed."}
{"Author": "Stephen Trahan", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Notifications issues appear to be fixed (if fixed means no notifications for the thermostat?). Away mode doesn't activate despite my using my phone for Home/Away Assist. I've waited over 2 hours and nothing happens. At least it knows when I'm home!"}
{"Author": "Jeff Banas", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Bad update, get notifications constantly. The notification will come up twice and then quickly go away. It's very annoying. Please fix this."}
{"Author": "Jason Toy", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Person alert\u200b are useless, pay for service and everyone leave cameras go on...great that's what I want but then I get an alert for each camera.... probably the biggest home/iot company disappointment."}
{"Author": "Bernard Briggs", "Date": "September 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Update September 2017: still horrible!  Randomly jumps to days and times as I try to watch specific times. I get black screens when I rotate to portrait mode all of the time. I also get frozen blank video while the audio still runs. The push to talk feature is so bad it may be better to not exist. Video playback is NOT HD even though it's set to record in HD all of the time.  And the home away feature simply doesn't work.  Great idea but poorly executed. Surprising for their marketing. Unfortunately, still the best option.  Maybe one day a young up start will give them a run for it and make them fight for their customers."}
{"Author": "Benjamin Moore", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Interface is nice. Works fine. I consistently have issues with touch feedback more so than with other apps. I have to tap around the numbers to select the high or low temperature. I have to keep tapping to select the zone I want to change. I'm not sure if it's just slow at processing the feedback or the sensitivity is off or the active area I need to touch is just that small. But it is slightly annoying.  Now that I have Nest outdoor cameras, I feel the UI is pretty terrible. I try to slide up and down to scrub time and it doesn't work at least half the time. Trying to expand to full screen doesn't work often. The tactile feedback is pretty erratic and annoying. But the single solution through Nest is enough that I'm sticking with it until something better comes along."}
{"Author": "William Hathaway", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Ok, nest is working great now. Saving energy, monitor cameras, combine with my echo ans other lights. To record to the cloud is a RIP OFF. Ring is cheaper. NEST is all about the dollar."}
{"Author": "Gregory Bodenheimer", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Needs some fine tuning with video history viewing on the mobile device. Still love the app and layout though. Would like to see live video feed on Android Wear and a home security system. Hopefully the announcement on the 20th of this month is about one of those things or, even better, both."}
{"Author": "Timothy McKay", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Great video, verbal communication with a person is horrible. Difficult for a person to hear, audio shuts off so it doesn't handle two way communication well. During the trial period and having set up alert areas performance was spotty."}
{"Author": "Mihajlo Veselinovic", "Date": "September 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App is terrible, double alerts, sucks at trying to scroll thru timeline, it has a mind of its own and keeps going all over place, whenever I open the app it ends up on one of the cameras view instead of main menu. When I switched the app to horizontal view it's cuts off the view, just terrible  on Samsung S8+. Looking for camera replacement even after I invested into nest cameras over $1,000 and pay them monthly plus another $1,000 for thermostats and nest protects. They can't get the app to work... terrible!"}
{"Author": "Samuel E Caballero", "Date": "September 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App no longer works with home/away assist. Keeps turning on when I'm home - S7Edge on Nougat. Updated to the Note 8 running on Android 7.1.1 and the app can't even use Home/Away Assist. I don't understand why you guys can't get this right. Worse part is your tech support is unhelpful and unknowledgeable."}
{"Author": "Jason Meeks", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I enjoy the app.   Does what it needs to do.   I now get double notifications, so yeah that's a bug that needs fixing.   Everyone would cry the app never updates, or cry when something wrong happens.  No one's every happy.  That's the point of feedback.   Again, I think the app works great.  Can see the camera feed, adjust house temp.   About nest cameras.  They tell you that it requires a decent speed Wi-Fi connection and to test locations to make sure your happy with the feed.  I have 2 routers in my house, 1 for the cameras and a few upstairs things and 1 for the basement stuff.  So when reading reviews and comments , be sure to wonder if common sense was used or just someone crying cause they aren't happy."}
{"Author": "Mario Martinez", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The latest update broke my activity zone notifications. I tried removing and reinstalling all my cameras and it's still messed up. Customer service was no help resolving the issue. I hope a future update fixes it.  Edit #1: I finally discovered (on my own) what the issue is. Unless you have \"person seen\" activated, you will not get notifications in an activity zone when someone walks by. With this option turned off, you will only get notifications for motion. For example: a bird flying by or waving your hand directly in front of the camera. This is extremely unfortunate for people who only want person seen notifications in specific activity zone instead of in the entire camera's field of vision. For example: a camera pointing outside where people regularly walk by, but you are only interested in notifications in a specific zone. The only other option is to turn on \"person seen\" and get a million notifications throughout the day and hope that one of them is within the activity zone you actually care about. I really hope they fix this so \"person seen\" is a unique option for each activity zone instead of the camera overall. Currently, it's a broken feature. Edit #2: still no good feedback from Nest on how to solve the notification issues. I've had to \"hack\" my cameras by smudging/dirtying the lens making the video quality blurry. This tricks the camera into not recognizing if a person walks in an activity zone. Instead, it only sees it as motion which results in the notifications I want. Pretty sad that I have to do this in order to get a simple feature to work. Edit #3: I unsubscribed from Nest Aware since there is still an issue with motion alerts and person alerts. No point in throwing away money."}
{"Author": "Mark B Ouellet", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Love the app.  Set the temp while away and turn up the heat on your way home from work in the winter.  Keeps use of your heat to a minimum by learning your schedule!"}
{"Author": "Emmet Cahill", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Cam notifications, email and app, are coming in at least ten minutes after the event, it makes it useless as a security device. Scrubbing through the timeline is hit and miss as regards behaviour on the S7. Feels like an inferior product"}
{"Author": "Patrick Kajirian", "Date": "September 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's good to see Android O channel notifications support. Any chance we can get Picture-in-Picture support as well?"}
{"Author": "Andy M", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Live video quality is comparable to Lyric and ZModo. Not any better, not any worse. The only way to get any recorded video is with a paid monthly subscription! Sure wish they made that clear before buying it. The schedule feature only turns the camera on and off, not the notifications. Why do I need a notification that I just walked in front of the camera while at home? Also when at 'Home' the camera recording is completely turned off. Hey Nest, ever heard of a HOME INVASIONS? Yes s#it does happen when people are at home and are relying on the camera to capture it. This app/camera is missing all the little features that actually give the user security and comfort. Several cheaper options out there for spying on the family dog, that's all this one is reliably good for."}
{"Author": "David Fink", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app is being used for the outdoor cameras. This app is maddeningly cumbersome. Useablity, on rewinding, rotating  screen to see content skips to different time events. Talk back is barely functional due to lag, interface not responding and major lag on Mic shutting off in time to hear persons response assuming you can get it to work. They need to get someone to real world test this app because it's a message for cameras. I believe it functioned better before an update but not sure. I suspect Ring is a better product. Nest needs to fix this app for the camera as it's functionality as a security camera is not working in real-time 2-way device. More stars will be earned if they can get their act together."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Pathetic is too good of a word to describe this app. Scrolling to view events is cumbersome at best and when you finally locate what you want to see it takes you back to live mode."}
{"Author": "charanjeev sawhney", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Over all its very great but after the recent update with camera talk button holding option has a problem . When talk button is released it takes a while ( delay) before I can hear the other person at door usually by then they have already finished talking which is never heard . I never had such issue with previous version ( hold to talk ). Can u please look into this as it's very important and annoying ."}
{"Author": "Ian S", "Date": "September 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It can be very frustrating trying fast forward/rewind 15 seconds on videos, and almost impossible to click a thumbnail.....but its.still 100x better than their horrid website video player. Also can be slow to load a stream."}
