{"Author": "Nigel D'Souza", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have been interested in using a WiFi connected thermostat for a couple of years and after doing quite a lot of research found that the nest would be the best and easiest for my home. Others would have required extra wiring. I've been using nest for 3.5 months and am happy with the product. App load time is good and the changes to temp/fan run times using the app is almost instant. Recommended."}
{"Author": "Jamie Dunn", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Since the update home/away assist notifications now keep popping up momentarily on my phone and vanishes in a split second.  This is taking the \u00d7\u00d7\u00d7\u00d7 now. Very annoying.   The app and the thermostat itself also lacks alot of functions that i had previously in my honeywell chronotherm cm907. For a smart thermostat its functions are quite basic and not as good as it could be."}
{"Author": "Amar Roopah", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App is nice but as other users have reported, the latest update messed up the notification. I get 3 notifications for every single thing that the nest cam picks up. It gets really annoying. Fix this and I will change my rating to a 5 star."}
{"Author": "Luke S", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The latest update has caused issues with location. We are receiving alerts despite being at home. Also receiving multiple notifications, or a notification popping up then disappearing. Please revert the app back to the previous stable version"}
{"Author": "Robert Roots", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App is nice and I use it a lot, but it have been sending phantom notifications to me for the past week roughly 10 - 20 times a day for no explainable reason. Frustrating to say the least, especially when it is interrupting my sleep at night."}
{"Author": "V Lower", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Updated after having over a year. Reasons not to buy nest cams: you have no control over notifications, they believe that their \"smart\" notifications are all you need even though you're paying the bill. Second, you literally need gaming quality internet or your picture will be worthless. I can't make out faces that are 7 or more feet away. I've called them, I've paid for better internet, no improvement. I won't even comment on the app because it's worthless due to the crappy cameras. Find another way, make sure you get what you pay for."}
{"Author": "Gregory Meiste", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The home auto away using phone location doesn't work reliability. If I have to check every day that the thermostat actually switched to away, then the feature is useless."}
{"Author": "Chris Walker", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Dropping from 4 stars back to 3. August 2017 update brings back the double notification sound for every single notification. Well done Nest, at least you had it fixed for a month or two before it broke again. Rotating from landscape back to portrait makes the feed jump to live view every time now. Again, it was fixed for a couple of updates, now broken again. As is always the case with Nest.... one step forward, two steps back."}
{"Author": "Adrian Roberts", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Just recently started having notification issues on my S8.  Notifications pop and and go away on their own.  This needs to be resolved ASAP.  This defeats the purpose of having an outdoor nestcam.  No security.  Why am I paying $15 a month for a service that doesn't work."}
{"Author": "Taylor Hardekopf", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I enjoy the app, however since the update happened I've been getting double notifications and a really spotty connection to one of my cameras. Once that's resolved it'll be 5 stars from me."}
