{"Author": "Ben Whitchurch", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App gives phantom notifications or double notifications. It only opens the video feed when pressing a notification sometimes. And please, please enable the option to disable vibrate in notifications. Please."}
{"Author": "Jon Bradley", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Constantly firing off notifications about it operating in the background on my pixel. Really really annoying."}
{"Author": "Nancy Carolyn", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "pan> Application and the nest thermostat have saved me money on my electric bill over the last 6 months. More than a 30% reduction in my electric bill. The Nest thermostat has already paid for itself twice. Amazing thermostat, easy-to-use app"}
{"Author": "Allen Ling", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Latest update now gives me triple notifications on my s8. Literally just passed my 30 day return period. If this happened during the 30 days I never would have kept it."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app is garbage and even worse with latest update. Like it was never even tested. Dropcam app has always been better. I read an article about the original developer and how he regrets ever selling the company because of how Google/Nest have completely neglected the platform. The new group is only interested in sales and has zero interest in supporting and improving the products beyond that. I have witnessed the decline in quality and service from Dropcam and am moving on. Disgusting to have the resources they do and not to utilize them by hiring good people to support their products/customers and by not investing in obviously needed improvements. Just read the real reviews, the ones that have similar complaints. The 5 star reviews with zero details are obviously created by Nest to boost their score...and how sad that they can't get above a measly 4.0. There is no way that this app is working well enough for anyone to rate it above a 1. Like I said, it's garbage. How anyone can feel good about working on this app and for this company is amazing. I would be too embarrassed to tell anyone where I worked."}
{"Author": "Grace Blakey", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Since the update there has been a double notification Bing for this app. Happens on both my husband's and my phone. Please fix."}
