{"Author": "Daniel Pearson", "Date": "August 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Wake up alarm can't be set for the next like 12 hours. If you want to have the lights go on in the morning and it's within like 12 hours of when you need them to, good luck. Piece of garbage coding keeps them from working."}
{"Author": "Tre Murillo", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app and the accompanying Widget both feel like alpha versions. Unintuitive UX, and the widget doesn't toggle lamps on the first tap, so if you're not at home there is no guarantee it is on/off when you think it is."}
{"Author": "Mick Hood", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app works well, and has great features. It does keep popping up saying 'Out of home' connection quite regularly whilst I'm at home if I use my WiFi extender. The Hue hub is direct wired to my Sky Hub and signal strength is pretty good throughout the house so I don't know why. Love the home and away routines; it's great to come home to light so I'm not blind when I go indoors lol. Great work, Philips. Next please add G9 smart bulbs and I'll be happy. Also, just a thought, add a way to make one light fitting/location include multiple bulbs so they can sync the same way. Some light fittings have more than one bulb."}
{"Author": "TS Brookhouse", "Date": "August 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Where the hell did light recipes go?? Or the ability to add your own and to customize which lights turn which color? This hamfisted approach flies in the face of why I started using Hue lights in the first place. Very glad the old app is still available; this one is complete garbage."}
{"Author": "Anna Stockel", "Date": "August 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Needed more functionality than Hue 1, not less.  What was the point of releasing this?  Plus, when I run the much better Hue 1 app it bugs me to update.   For the price of these lights and lots of IOT companies sprouting, Philips really needs to get on the ball!"}
{"Author": "Andy M\u00fcller", "Date": "August 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I was pleasantly surprised with the latest update. Finally we have timers back that were a missing feature still from the first app. I'll give ya another star for that. Now just give back the ability to fade out the lights during the timer and we will be back where the old app stopped."}
{"Author": "Psychokill", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I'll give this five stars when we can add existing lights to other rooms.  My living room is 31 feet long so i made it into two rooms so i can control half the lights but if i want to turn them all on at once,  i can't because i can't add them all together ad one big room."}
{"Author": "Tim Midgett", "Date": "August 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Incompatible with duel band routers. If your router has 5ghtz band, you'll only be able to use the app in Out of Home mode, which is a considerable handicap as you can't use many of the apps features in out off home. Customer support told me that they do not not intend to correct this shortcoming."}
{"Author": "Sunil Magesh", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Sometimes lights turn on and off by themselves.... Just happened about 3 times... within 5 min? Could there be a privacy breach? Could to let me know what caused it?   Labs are hard to get to."}
{"Author": "Alexander Youngblood", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I waited until I was used to this app. The old at was bad and this one is worse. We lost features, setting up routines is annoying, navigation is convoluted, and the app minimizes to a browser too log in. Then it doesn't remember I logged in later.  In essence, it feels like they either didn't listen to their UI/UX designers, or those designers were completely incompetent/non-existent. I hate this app."}
{"Author": "Scott Akerman", "Date": "August 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worked fine until latest updates and now the wake up routine doesn't reliably work. I've tried deleting and remaking routines but it hasn't fixed it. Really annoying since that's how I used to wake up."}
{"Author": "Albin Gjoka", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Should be able to enable random colors as a scene. I also miss the option to select a certain scene to be used at an specific time if i turn on my lights.(for example: after 22:00h i want my lights to be dimmer if i turn them on and in the morning backto brigbt)"}
{"Author": "M. Henry", "Date": "August 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Way too many updates. It's frustrating how many times I have to wait while this app updates. I just want to turn my light on or off"}
{"Author": "Paul Hargrove", "Date": "October 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Used to work OK ish.. but now Android app says no Hue detected and can't find the bridge but iOS is working fine... also hate the new icon.  I have uninstalled and reinstalled on android but still can't find the bridge."}
{"Author": "Christian Heinbockel", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is a huge step down from the first gen hue app. Not user friendly at all. This is the only app I have rated all year. For a 5 star review please allow all bulbs to be changed simultaneously (like the first generation Hue app) instead of individually."}
{"Author": "Jon Koluder", "Date": "August 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It worked great until the most recent update, now the wake up routine works only when it wants to. I used to use it as my alarm until it it became unreliable."}
{"Author": "Jeremy Claisse", "Date": "August 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The motion sensor has a major flaw please fix in update. You cannot have different auto off settings during the day and night modes. So if you want your lights hooked up to the sensor to automatically turn off after 10 mins at night, that will also have to happen during the day too turning off the lights after 10 min when you want them to stay on throughout the day."}
{"Author": "Rob D", "Date": "September 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not sure why but the app has no menu, only a help button and a search button. Help only shows how to connect to the bridge. I need remote access."}
{"Author": "Clay Colding", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Great app. Support tons of lights and tons of setting in a simple and logical setup configuration. If you're looking for something that your grandma can set up, I'm sure they have pretty Christmas lights that flicker on their own at walmart. Seriously. As long as you know how to think and problem solve, this app will allow you to do anything you could ever want and more."}
{"Author": "John R Perry", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Did you guys have an update recently because the sensors rarely work anymore. I did a factory reset and I'm still having issues."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Crude home automation app: no multiuser features, limited access to hardware features, widgets have highly restricted features. Hue hardware is good, software seems like something created internally to support QA during early stages of development."}
{"Author": "Thomas Crouch", "Date": "August 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App works great. Very responsive and lots of features. Google home functionality is a bit hit or miss sometimes in respect to turning on/off lights but doubt this is Philips problem. Price is too high but still a great product."}
{"Author": "Joe Martinez", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Previously rated 5 star but no longer. I really enjoyed the Hue system.  Worked really well until the rescent software update.  My 'routines' no longer work.  I use an Android phone.  Please fix this soon   :("}
{"Author": "Levon Shahumyan", "Date": "August 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Away routine does not trigger when I go away by car or taxi - quickly, but does whey I go slowly by foot. Home routine behaves the same way when I come back by car or foot respectively."}
{"Author": "Olivier Keun", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Home &amp; away (geofencing) doesn't work at all, used to work in an earlier version. Needs more debugging info since it's completely unclear why things don't work. Location based sunset and sunrise is a much needed  function, fixed time routines are really inconvenient for year round usage."}
{"Author": "tamie gragg", "Date": "August 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It worked great up till a week ago. We have had this system for over a year. Now it cannot find the hub.  Uninstalled and reinstalled but still nothing.   Can anybody help???"}
{"Author": "Donal Fleming", "Date": "August 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can't connect when out of house.  It's mediocre overall compared to, say, the Nest app and website. For example you can't see the schedule for a light or room in one place? But now I can no longer connect when not at home on my wifi? I can connect from the website, but that is really limited. Given how expensive the bulbs are this is very frustrating."}
{"Author": "YC Tan", "Date": "August 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "While i was able to pair my bridge, i was unable to do so when i tried to login to my hue acct and pair. Something with the hue acct login process is broken. Please fix it."}
{"Author": "Chuck Gittins", "Date": "August 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Wow, why would you make the app less functional!  It used to have many built in scenes and a way to add more. Now there are only a few built-in scenes and NO WAY TO ADD MORE?? Who came up with this update?   They should be fired."}
{"Author": "Sean Haywood", "Date": "October 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "s some work.</span> For the price of these things, this app should have been R&amp;D better. And as someone else said. The Home and away functionality does not work."}
{"Author": "J Riza", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This lights are amazing, I recently had to get surgery and cant move to much from my bed for the time being. I installed these around the house and use my google home to voice activate the lighting so I dont have to get up and its helped alot. The app works well and looks good. Great way to set up your home for smart capabilities"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "October 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Gen 1 app is still far superior. Scenes are per room and lights are locked to a single room. The widgets are unreliable."}
{"Author": "Tim Tam", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "To Philips credit, this app has improved greatly over time. It has a clean interface, has an excellent widget implementation, and is reasonably well featured. It would be great to see rooms replaced (or augmented) with groups, with lights being allowed in more than one group. It would be nice to trigger routines from a widget button, not just a time of day. It would be nice to have a \"fade off\" option, like in the win 10 app \"hue dynamic\". And it would be nice to expose the advanced tap and dimmer programming seen in other apps. But so far so good, it's the only hue app on my phone. I use \"hue dynamic\" to program my dimmers and taps."}
{"Author": "Adam DeYoung", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "When the lights work, they work great. When they don't, you're on message boards at 4 am praying you find a way to shut them off. Things are like Skynet."}
{"Author": "J", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's good when it works. Login issues on occasion. Routines do not work if lights are in a dimmed state. More specifically less than 20%. Please fix this."}
{"Author": "Not-so-Irish-Potato", "Date": "August 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app slows down my phone when installed by around 3x. As soon as I uninstall it, its back to normal speed. Otherwise, app is great."}
{"Author": "Rob Clements", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Networking is terrible. Do you want lights whenever you please as opposed to when all of the networking layers are acting exactly as the Phillips engineers thought they should be  in whatever cave they work out of? Don't buy these! You'll be left in the dark."}
{"Author": "Alexei Godek", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Why do routines work for one day but not this next? Ridiculous"}
{"Author": "James Graham", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Unable to log in to my account which is linked to Google. Select the correct option, grant permissions then I get a blank screen and it doesn't log in. Also my lights seem to randomly come on and fade out too."}
{"Author": "Dan Gascoyne", "Date": "October 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Lack of imagination. When you think about it everything is a routine so there's really no need for 3 separate sections (Got to sleep, Wake up and Routines).  Oddly Routines will not wake my lights up so rendering them redundant.  Another thing that's frustrating is that only routines allow you to assign a scene.  I'd like to see everything under routines with complete control with regards to brightness, light selection, colour changing on and off times.  Let users be as elaborate as their imagination allows or more importantly there lifestyle dictates."}
{"Author": "Jeevanand Kuharaj", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Set the beacon to turn on lights when arriving after sunset. Doesn't work on Samsung S8. But Sleep as Android can in the morning every day! This is a Bad App!"}
{"Author": "Alex Ottway", "Date": "October 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The inability to do a slow fade (eg 5 seconds from full to off) is breathtaking by its absence. If I want an abrupt change I'll just use an old fashioned (and inexpensive) switch. With a \"cutting edge\" lighting controller, this is a staggering omission. Please can you look into this?"}
{"Author": "Alex Memije", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Loving the lights and the app. Up until the recent update my lights are sometimes unreachable.. then recently the lights are flickering on and off! What's going on!"}
{"Author": "Page Nelson", "Date": "October 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Why does this update my lights so often? And why do updates take sooooo long!?! It makes no sense to me. Every time I go to use this app to adjust some lights, it forces me to do an update that takes well over 5 mins...  Anyway, I really expected a much better design / interface than what appears here. Perhaps one of their hundreds of updates will one day solve this problem."}
{"Author": "Michael Mosley", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My biggest problem is with the widget. It has great customization when it comes to making buttons, but it looks really bad. The buttons differentiate themselves enough on their own from the wallpaper, but it's all placed on a background that isn't transparent and has a bar over the top. Imagine if every app on your home screen was in box with a darker bar over it with the name. It would look very over complicated. The only thing you should see is the button and the name. There are also other possibilities for expansion like a dimmer slider or color wheel, but those too should be implemented without any graphical salad behind it."}
{"Author": "Saif Azeez", "Date": "August 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have no problem with this app or the lights, you need to check your network setup, also make sure no interference or any issues with your wifi router."}
{"Author": "Andrew R", "Date": "August 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I can't believe it, after 2 years we finally have Randomization!  Hue 2.0 is finally a fully functioning app."}
{"Author": "Suraj Baadkar", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Lot of features In routine don't work as intended. It keeps randomly turning off. Location detect doesn't work on my Android. Works fine on my wife's iPhone."}
{"Author": "James Stables", "Date": "August 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Good reliable app offering decent control of the hue lights. It's very easy to connect them and control them. For more detailed settings additional apps are required but this is good for the basics."}
{"Author": "Andre Plaisant", "Date": "August 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not sure why so many low ratings. Works great and easy to operate. The only thing missing in my opinion is the ability to have  Labs utilities available directly from scenes"}
{"Author": "Chad Walker", "Date": "September 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Good hardware, awful software. And it keeps getting worse. Glad I didn't buy too far in with Hue."}
{"Author": "Jon Agsalud", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "updated app and my bridge lost internet connection. I've done a factory reset 3 times and my app cannot find my bridge"}
{"Author": "Bil Cooper", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app works perfect for me. The newest update improves Routines to allow turning lights off in same routine as turning them on rather than having to create a separate routine to turn lights off. I don't get the low rating for this app. I have never had a problem with the Hue lights app and it is very versatile. Works great over cellular when away from home."}
{"Author": "Jasmin Contreras", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Ever since the most recent update, ALL of my lights turn off/dim to 1%/turn on at random times even with no routines configured at all. Truly maddening to wake up at off hours to every light on at full brightness or to be in the middle of something when all the lights suddenly turn off!!"}
{"Author": "jayant sood", "Date": "August 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not able to connect online as fails to find the bridge. With WiFi works but away from home feature not able to access."}
{"Author": "matthias aka", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Nice app but it would be better if I could use bixby voice control without any other hubs, the home and away isn't working. Sometimes they do work and switch on but only 2 hours after I came home and when I'm already sleeping..."}
{"Author": "Giles Meehan", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Excellent lights, terrible app  I think the programmers must have smoked a bit too much of something weird to come up with such an unintuitive app so lacking in function."}
{"Author": "RoyaleWchz", "Date": "August 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Tired of \"giving the app another try\" after updates. This is a very very poorly designed app and extremely buggy. I've tried so many times to give it another go.  Just use smartthings to control hue, this app is awful."}
{"Author": "Brandon Jack", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can you guys make pairs of lights within rooms that can be turned on together such as a overhead light that takes 2 lightbulbs. So you don't have to individually switch on each light in the fixture."}
{"Author": "Toni Niemi", "Date": "September 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The motion sensor will shut off lights after a few minutes when motion isn't detected even in daytime when it's set to not trigger any lights during the day. Please add an option to shut down lights after a few minutes only at night."}
{"Author": "\u6881\u591a\u9ed8", "Date": "August 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Cannot find the bridge even after updating. Other apps can find the bridge! But still cannot be connected."}
{"Author": "Kyle Allen", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Slow, unreliable, and half the time it just says \"no hue connection\" even though me and the lights are on the same network and I'm logged in. Horrible app design."}
{"Author": "Laurence Hawker", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Only have a couple of lights so far and the app has been solid. Not sure of the bad reviews unless they were from early reviews. Does need a widget for individual bed side lights, we have the dimmer mounted between us though."}
{"Author": "James Holder", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Following the recent update to Oreo, my app seems to keep telling my bridge that I'm away from and returning home when I haven't moved, meaning the light keep going on / off."}
{"Author": "Sonya Pietrogiacomo", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not user-friendly app. Cannot figure out how to accurately enter lights on app. No menu, no help. I entered my lights into app then discovered there are apparently preset named rooms(?) I'm not even sure. Only control lights through google. Terrible app for Phillips."}
{"Author": "Michael Calore", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's a basic system to control Hue lights, however it lacks depth and tends to be bulky. This is especially true when dealing with more complex logic (multiple sets of rules/devices), working with Hue Labs (not native to app) and certain hardware (like pre-existing dimmer switches).    While it lacks in certain areas, the app is essential in connecting and starting to use your Hue system."}
{"Author": "Leif Larson", "Date": "August 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "How do I pay $400 to Phillips for the hue setup in my house and this app and their support is junk but I can buy an app for $3 that does everything?"}
{"Author": "Kenneth Castano", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "after the most recent update, my hue bridge stopped connecting to my app :/ now my lights are stuck to the purple setting I had before they stopped working"}
{"Author": "Eric Jaeger", "Date": "August 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "5star once they let you put lights in more than one room.  Sub-rooms, Floors, and grouping colored lights together would be awesome."}
{"Author": "john doy", "Date": "August 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's says my Hue needs an update but nothing happens and app won't proceed. My Hue lights are all switched on at the moment and app won't allow me to switch them off"}
{"Author": "Levi Criswell", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Horrible app. Never connects. Ever. Lovely being without your lights because of a horrible app"}
{"Author": "Mike Smithson", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Rarely Works. Will only find one of 5 lights. Will only find 3 of 5 lights. Bridge will be be responding. MUST BE HOME TO DO ANYTHING WITH THE LIGHTS. Unlike WeMo where you can be anywhere in the world and change your lights. For the most part, expensive lightbulbs you might be able to change sometimes."}
{"Author": "Diar Hassan", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have an issue with this. For some reason google assistant can't set the scene :/. After saying the \"okay google turn scene to x\", it replies \"okay setting scene to x\". But nothing happens"}
{"Author": "Enn Singh", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can't sign in for controlling while out of the WiFi range. The screen goes blank when I try to do that. Anyone has a fix?"}
{"Author": "Luke Marris", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Just got the lights. This app is surprisingly sluggish. I also cannot find the room scenes tab as advertised above?"}
{"Author": "Richard S", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Finally the app works as described. Very happy now the home and away feature works"}
{"Author": "Andrea Goodman", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The lights for alarms dont gradually turn on, they just turn on super bright. And it would be super cool to set room colors other then that these lights are badass"}
{"Author": "John Adams", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Sleep setting does not fade lights at all. End up having to turn them off with the app. Worked about a week"}
{"Author": "Christian Feliciano", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Oh my God they turned on at random drive me crazy"}
{"Author": "Drew Miller", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Slow when I'm at home and \"no hue connection\" when I'm away. I expect a lot more for an app that accompanies hundreds of dollars of light bulbs."}
{"Author": "Matt Langis", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works good overall, but with iOS it's integrated into the control panel for easy access. Why can't it be integrated into the pull down quick settings or at least a widget"}
{"Author": "Louis-Antoine Caron", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Cannot just connect with account to synchronize with new phone, you absolutely have to press the button But other than that, it's a great and easy to use app and it's really responsive."}
{"Author": "xPazz Adi", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Pathetic, can't even find my lights now, not even after a reset and not even after adding manually the serial number, thanks."}
{"Author": "Bren Simpson", "Date": "August 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Temperamental and unreliable. Only works periodically. GPS automatic turn on and off doesn't work at all. Poor"}
{"Author": "Gerald Haskell", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Wake up feature does not work.  I'm using pixel phone. 3 gen lights"}
{"Author": "Erik Feketefoldi", "Date": "September 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Everytime when powered off the bulb will go back to a hidious yellowish light temperature."}
{"Author": "Erling Pettersen", "Date": "October 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Ok app, but broken.  Many scenes,  ie. Relax, does not work. Wake up and sleep timers does nothing."}
{"Author": "Clint Jones", "Date": "October 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Never connects to the bridge. I have to reinstall it several times and it still doesn't work."}
{"Author": "Isaac Busch", "Date": "August 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Latest update is now crashing my phone every time I open the app"}
{"Author": "TrollTechRUS", "Date": "August 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Wish it was easier to enter scenes, edit them including being able to edit image's  used for scenes. A realistic candle light mode would be amazing as well. Otherwise, fairly satisfied."}
{"Author": "Paul Field", "Date": "August 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Just needs a snappier way of accessing multiple hubs, rather than having to spend half your life negotiating the menus to switch back and forward between them"}
{"Author": "Dan Carpenter", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Update is broken. Says downloading for 12+ hours now.  There's always glitches."}
{"Author": "Brian Burwell", "Date": "August 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app seems to work fine, but I can't log into my account. When I put in my email and password it says it can't find an account with those credentials."}
{"Author": "Riggy Riggs", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "47mb? Come on. Totally unwarranted app size. What's it all for? Switching a light on."}
