{"Author": "", "Date": "July 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "what is up with this update. every time and  as of right now my app has been updating for 30+ minutes. After spending 2k on these bulbs 2 years ago in honestly fu of regrets. i truly wish i had gone with the other smart led bulbs. better app, brighter bulbs, and better colors. please fix this app"}
{"Author": "Erick Hueck", "Date": "June 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app is okay, the bulbs themselves are awesome! But this app can be glitchy sometimes and Phillips Hue should fix it. Also, it works fine on my galaxy note 5 phone but impossible to use on my Amazon fire tablet and customer services doesn't reply to my emails about it. Again, the light bulbs are great but the app is \"okay\""}
{"Author": "Luc Id", "Date": "June 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "\"App functionality is limited until you update\" I get this message nearly every week and can't use app until it updates. I rarely give bad reviews but I have never been so ipset with an app before. Geuss I will stick to alternative hue apps as this one never seems to improve despite constant bad reviews."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "July 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is the most bug-filled application I have ever used. I hope Philips doesn't employ the same level of QA on their products as they do with their software.  After installing Bridge updates, the app informs you perpetually that there is still an update to apply; The home screen widget does not correctly save settings, and subsequent app updates cause the widget and its settings to be erased."}
{"Author": "Sammy Katta", "Date": "July 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Unusable for the past couple weeks. Keeps telling me functionality is limited until I update the app, and when it checks, it finds no updates but still doesn't let me use the app. Can't change my wake or sleep schedules, or do anything other than turn my lights off and on."}
{"Author": "Rishi Patel", "Date": "June 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "location feature seems problematic. after recents updates the 'leavin home' section doesn't allow me to uncheck the bedroom and now my lights keep randomly turning off. was good before even though i didnt use this feature that never worked. other than that its fine i have a backup lamp"}
{"Author": "George Chung", "Date": "June 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The most recent update threatens to limit the functionality of this app. So updated I did. Guess what? The update message persists, still limiting the app to turning all lights on or off with no full functionality. It's basically stuck in a loop of trying to update, finding the app up to date, and still having no full functionality. This is absurdly terrible."}
{"Author": "liam bilich", "Date": "July 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "lousy, you cannot make light belong to more then one room. and when you do, you lose all the presets you had since the lights are removed from other rooms and the presets simply void. The app was ordered by philips from q contractor to give a basic app, problem is that its quite bad. also slow and does not recognize the bridge, so you need to close it, open again, and it works, sometimes more then twice is needed. you'll be disappointed , but most of the others are even less functional and very cumbersome and slow."}
{"Author": "Sagar Dhawan", "Date": "July 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "When \"ok google\" gets to your lights faster than the official app, you know you've got some work to do. Also, it's been over a year now and geo fencing still doesn't work.. Ffs.. The switch keeps going to the off position on its own."}
{"Author": "Francois B.", "Date": "June 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Seriously limits what the hue bulbs should be able to do.  It was possible before to create scenes that controlled all the lights.  Now you are limited to do this on a room by room basis only.  Meaning the dimmers are extremely limited and it's impossible to set moods for a whole apartment with one click.  Simply a terrible app.  Since they've stopped supporting scenes from the v1 app, this has crippled hue bulbs in home automation. As live in a loft, this app makes me want to return everything."}
{"Author": "Ramon Vizcarra", "Date": "June 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "No matter how many times I try to login to My Hue Account, it still fails. One of the features I was looking forward to the most and it has never worked. Sad."}
{"Author": "Leon Mohorovic", "Date": "July 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Honestly don't know why so many negative reviews... I just got this and the lights and it is fantastic! Could not be happier. Just make sure your network is set up properly so you don't run into issues."}
