{"Author": "J Caine", "Date": "July 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I read the description of the gen 1 app when it turned grey and it said everyone anticipating second gen app but its significantly lacking in features and functionality.  I definitely prefer the gen 1 app so far.  I can no longer choose specific colors from the scenes with drop arrows, can't share scenes from the gen 1 app? Maybe merge the two apps together so we don't have to keep switching?...  And why does it think I'm in Khazikstan? It won't maintain my location. Hopefully it's a work in progress.  Update: dropped to 2 stars because i keep setting a light and it won't maintain the color i set. This picture crappy app. I keep trying and hoping it'll get better but it keeps reminding me why I still only use the gen 1 app."}
{"Author": "Jon McLaren", "Date": "July 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Lights are cool, set up is easy but lights seem to turn on randomly in the middle of the night even though they are not scheduled to. It's annoying waking up at 3 am because your lights decided to turn on."}
{"Author": "Christian Odom", "Date": "July 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The user interface is great, but the functionality is lacking.  Compared to third party apps like \"Hue Pro\", this app is sub par.  This is surprising as the hardware is all yours.  I've been looking at the network traffic trying to figure out what it's going wrong.  I've adjusted router settings, but nothing has helped like switching apps.  The problem is typically the connection to the hub.  Often I have to toggle on/off up to 30 times before the light finally responds.  Color changes often stop responding after the first change.  Third part apps don't have this issue.  It's a shame as their user interfaces aren't as nice."}
{"Author": "Steve G", "Date": "July 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My hue works fine with hue pro, Logitech and lampshade. This app so slow, constantly drops connection. Widgets never work. Have problems with hue app with 5 different Android devices and 3 ios devices. Other apps and products work fine."}
{"Author": "Rory Manzaroli", "Date": "July 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Pretty basic but seems reliable and functional. However, PLEASE move the green 'connected' banner to the bottom of the screen or put it in the nav bar. Every time I open the app it pops up and moves the entire list of rooms down slightly making it fiddly to dim or select the lights."}
