{"Author": "Chris Wojno", "Date": "July 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Has loads of problems. It forgets light setting and refused to save geofencing options. I'd set them and save them, when I returned to the screen, the settings were as though I never put them in. Geofencing is broken and has never worked, which was a selling feature for the lights. It feels like a bait and switch. App interface is slow and clunky. Version one was far superior. They should trash this and revert back to the version they had years ago. Very poor but operates with Google home after some non intuitive and poorly documented steps"}
