{"Author": "OneOkami", "Date": "July 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I don't ask for TOO MUCH out of managing my bulbs right now but location-aware automation is one of the features I was sold on and from what I now understand, Philips has neglected to fix the issue on Android for at least the better part of a YEAR despite numerous complaints.  And I can tell you as an iPad user location-aware works just fine on iOS.  That is, quite simply, tremendously disrespectful to Android customers and very unprofessional.  I do love the concept of this product, it's a great idea, but the way Philips had handled this issue, which is to say, basically ignoring well-paying customers who can't use their broken products the way it was advertised, leaves a bad taste in my mouth with this company.  I've seen no sort of explanation or apology from Philips about this.  Just a disgusting display of apathy given a glaringly broken significant feature that has remained that way for months and months months.  If someone can think of a legitimate excuse for that please let me know.  EDIT:  Downgraded to one star.  No excuse for them to take THIS long to fix the Geofencing.  You don't take YEARS to fix a bug if you really cared.  As a customer I'm disgusted.  EDIT 2:  The broken Geofencing fix was long overdue (and that's an understatement) but it is here and after spending some time with it I finally feel like I have the product I paid good money for and updated my rating accordingly."}
