{"Author": "Felix Andersson", "Date": "July 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "\"App functionality is limited until you update\" - hey, you know what would be great? ACTUALLY BEING ABLE TO UPDATE"}
{"Author": "Robert Rogier", "Date": "July 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app took only the name of its predecessor. The actual usability is awful. The original version of this app was far easier to use, manage, and understand. (My review of that app is a Shakespearean soliloquy.) This one will be in modern English and hopefully easy for Philip's (if they even read these) to understand. In short, THIS APP IS TERRIBLE!!! I don't give a lot of negative reviews not do I type in all caps much, but this app however, required a more direct approach. Philip's took a wonderfully functional, not without flaws but functional, and gave us this. The new app is convoluted, with many flaws. To list a small few :  - Control of individual lights is much more difficult. I don't always want every light in a room on.   - The entire concept of the \"scenes\" is poorly executed and not useful.   - Setup and modification of add-on switches and controls is beyond bad. store I'll stop there because I have better things to do with my day than audit a horrible app. It's really telling when the gen 1 version of the app has a 3.6 rating in the store currently, while the \"upgrade\" is at 2.9. Really, consider moving the team who created this to another part of your businesses and bring back the original team to update the old app. While there are far superior pay apps out there, I shouldn't have to buy an app just to get a usable product."}
