{"Author": "Doctor Doom", "Date": "June 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "For people having problems with the widget, try turning off power saving mode to see of it works. I was constsntly getting \"not connected to hue bridge\" after recently changing my Galaxy S7 to use the medium power saving profile. For those who can't change there name of the widget, try selecting your scene first and then setting the name and click save. It works perfectly for me."}
{"Author": "Saad Mohammad", "Date": "June 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Missed opportunities here. This is one of the very few apps that CAN be capable of doing so much more, but it just doesn't deliver outside the basics. Come on guys! Clearly the devs are not getting the push or resources to provide us with a better app. Think about smart lights 10 years from now. What do you want it to do? Make it happen now and use it in your company's marketing. Show the world why they need smart light bulbs and why you are the best. Don't wait for someone else to do it.. because it's going to happen with or without hue bulbs."}
