{"Author": "Art Sprague", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's still an unreliable app. Setting/resetting a device's network connection rarely works as it's supposed to.  I've had these a few years now. I've had to throw some out because the plastic melted slightly when using with a 1500 watt heater. The app used to be real flaky and devices would randomly disappear.  For better automation, try using the app that has a desk on it, formerly known as WeMo Manager."}
