{"Author": "Onel Benjamin", "Date": "October 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Hands down - the worst app I've used in my life. Oh, and trying to connect to Google Home... Don't even start me. I've connect a million other things to Google Home, never had a problem. But I don't even know why people would pay money for Wemo."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is a terribly developed app. Belkin has a long long way to go. The insight and regular outlet should be about $20 and no more if they aren't going to produce an app that works right or is finnicky like this one. Really it is unacceptable to ask this much for spotty or terrible functionality."}
{"Author": "Justin S", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have a love hate relationship with this app. When it works it's good, but when it doesn't want to its a nightmare. I have 4 bulbs, 2 air purifiers and all worked see less for 2 weeks. Now it can only see one bulb and 1 purifier. If I turn one on the app crashes..."}
{"Author": "Chris Hanaway", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Very unreliable. Regularly loses connection. Plug has been \"upgrading\" now for 45 minutes. I don't recommend WeMo to anyone. My next smart plug won't be from Belkin."}
{"Author": "Randy Moy", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Easy to use but limited. Wish scheduling wasn't limited to a week. I hook this up to a plug that turns on something to prevent moisture buildup to the HVAC unit in my attic. Ideally would like to schedule to turn on in winter and off during spring."}
{"Author": "Alec Simonson", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not reliable.  The firmware never upgraded since Day 1.  The rules sometimes work, sometimes don't.  I turned off a rule while on vacation and came home to find the 1500 watt coffee maker on.  May have been on for 10 days....who knows.  The software said it was on for 4mins, which was absurd because it was fully hot.  What I worry about most is that the random on/off of important appliances may cause those items to break."}
{"Author": "John Horgan", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worked well at first and saved a lot of money on our heating bill. Had to reconnect because the socket was plugged out (not needed) now its hopeless tells you its connected but when you try to switch it on its not actually connected. Have tried everything. Really disappointed !!!"}
{"Author": "Yf Jugy", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "No way to get through the install without setting up a\"new\" device, and or being on the same wifi network as the device.  I already have an account on another device not with me, and wanted setup a new one while on vacation and can't. Sucks"}
{"Author": "Ken Troup", "Date": "September 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It totally ignores it's own rules. Everything about it is riddled with bugs. Read the Wemo forums to see the masses of problems before considering buying this overpriced junk."}
{"Author": "Finlay Stewart", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Remove the mandatory need to enter email immediately or I stop using the plugs, I didn't need to enter one an hour ago, why now? Plugs still unreliable, app still buggy"}
{"Author": "Lawrence Potts", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Unreliable - The wemo app has always been buggy for me and frustrating at times so I don't open it that often. I hope this fix makes it more user friendly."}
{"Author": "Joyce Yang", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I love it! Never have to worry about my house is too hot for my dogs ever again! Only give it a 4 stars because sometimes the app lags and won't turn on the device."}
{"Author": "Vishak Gopalan", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The Android app is simply subpar. Couldnt setup the device using my android phone but it worked like a charm when using the iOS app. Also once I added the device, it is only available on the phone through which I setup the device"}
{"Author": "Anibal Jodorcovsky", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Switch itself looks good and is easy to install. The application is really bad. There are so many bugs it's almost unusable. There are recurrent problems connecting to the switch, setting up rules, configuring other aspects and accessing other screens, with continuous hangs and crashes. Nice try but Belkin should really hire professional software developers if they want to succeed in this space. I'd look for another option."}
{"Author": "Bill Bathurst", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It worked ok with few bugs until they decided to do an unannounced \"firmware\" update that disabled my system and let a critical plug in the on position. Mechanical switches are more dependable"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "October 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Here's the only way a Belkin Wemo Lightbulb will ever give you satisfaction: Eventually it will frustrate you enough that you will be driven to smash the Wemo hub with a hammer. Seeing those shards of plastic casing and circuitry will give you a sense of delicious vengeance you have never felt before. And then you'll remember you spent $60+ on a product that should never have been released to the market."}
{"Author": "Matt Supernak", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Lost connection to WiFi due to maintenance and now it will not connect. I've reset my wemo's (2) and tried to connect it back over 50 times each one with no success. At first I loved them but now I want to throw them in the trash. THANKS BELKIN"}
{"Author": "Malcolm Smith", "Date": "August 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works ok but not great most of the time. If you miss the prompt to update firmware, it cannot manually be initiated.  Update: the remote access function no longer works for me. Reinstalling the app does not fix the problem. The app gives a \"failed\" prompt but no explaination for how to fix it."}
{"Author": "Calvin Page", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The setup for my wemo mini was slow and full of errors. The app, on my HTC 10, a flagship phone, is very laggy. Compared to the iOS app, it's very slow. You guys need to make fixing this app a top priority"}
{"Author": "Kenny Tower", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It could use a little bit of work. Fairly intuitive to set up. Seems to be a bit slow connecting and syncing your local network and with Amazon Echo. However it does go out on the internet for the sink and registering it so you can use it anywhere you have an internet connection."}
{"Author": "Kurt Smith", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Unlike other smart switches, even though it knows its location, having it turn on at dusk &amp; off at sunrise are not options. You have to give it specific on time and duration. Since the time of sunset is always changing,  have to constantly reprogram it. Software is very rudimentary."}
{"Author": "Timothy Hammond", "Date": "September 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's connection to Nest is horrible. I'm having to constantly de-authorize and reauthorize my Nest account to get it to work. Then it only works for a few hours."}
{"Author": "Doug Choy", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Already had the WiFi camera, so installing the wemo app recognized it and can control both products with the same app.  Plugged the TV into it, now I can control who watches/when. I am in control again!!!  Update:  When power goes out, or need to update wifi, this thing is the most frustrating experience ever!  Better products out there."}
{"Author": "John Laney", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App integrates well with wemo devices. But even though it says it has ifttt integration it is impossible to set it up. I can go to a webview for ifttt where the keyboard can't type in my username or password. I get a security warning when trying to sign in to ifttt with Google."}
{"Author": "Matt F", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Horrible interface.  Good luck reconnecting a switch easily if yours drops from the network on its own, because it has a hard time detecting it.  Also, I can't schedule anything and have it save it actually work.  It completely disappears if I closer the app and open it again.  I chatted with support and I told him there's a big with the app.  He said \"no\" and all he did was take me through the steps I already had been taking to create schedules.  Still didn't work in the end and wasted my time."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Device not show up in app. Tried many times (reset device, reinstalled app, rebooted phone...). Gave up and very disappointed..."}
{"Author": "Robert George", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I keep reading about WeMo so I bought the smart plug and BOY DOES THIS APP SUCK!!! OMG what a horrible app. This is made by kids and the people who gave it more than 1 star are technology illiterate or old people who aren't aware of how a smart product should function. Connecting the plug was horrible, had to click on \"try again\" numerous times. Once connected, tried to name it, it disconnects over and over again only to find out the name hasn't changed. Did that 5 times, then gave up and clicked on save. The app connected to my WiFi. Everything finally seemed to have worked. Linked it to Google home, tried to turn it on and off by voice, home acknowledges the command but nothing happens with the plug. Found out there's an update but no way to manually update it. Found a workaround, when I click on \"update now\" it takes me to a Window to update the device. Clicked on \"accept and update\" and guess what....nothing happens. Bought 3 of those plugs, returning them tomorrow!!! Unbelievable what this world is coming too."}
{"Author": "Dan Barron", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Rules do not work! I had defined many rules, now they do not appear in the app. The power of these \"smart\" devices is the rules. If the only way to turn these devices on and off is manually, then they are not \"smart\" devices."}
{"Author": "Dennis Hanks", "Date": "October 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Before trying the wemo, I tried a couple different manufactures of wifi timers and returned them because the would work reliably. I have had the wemo for 9 months now and they have worked perfectly.  I lost power a couple months ago for 6 hours, as soon as the power was restored the wemo was back on schedule and worked as programmed."}
{"Author": "Cindy Klemencic", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Working well, wish the rules linking to device was more intuitive, but once I got that nailed it was easy to add more.  Taking device pictures is not working, it says it saves but there is not a picture even after several attempts."}
{"Author": "Yi Guo", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Amazon Alexa has turned this sinking ship into something that is now functional and useful.  Use Alexa if you have it and skip this app.  The app still has many issues but things are slowly, very slowly getting better.  There's still the occasional unable to find all Wemos and the discovery is agrivatingly slow.  It would be nice if the app allowed you to set static IPs (like the MikeP Wemo Manager app) for each Wemo.  I have DHCP reservations for all mine.  This would speed up the process."}
{"Author": "Hillary McDougall", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I love everything except I can see my parents wemo controls when I'm at their house and vice versa and can control wemos as well. I assume this is because we know each other's wifi password and use the same app. This has got to be changed, an invasion of privacy to say the least. We don't know each other's wemo passwords but that doesn't matter because the app automatically finds whatever wemos are on the wifi. Please fix this."}
{"Author": "Antonie, Thor van Meurs", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Sometimes it is a little slow with commands from google home. But very good in general. The hard ware however could be a bit smaller so it fit better on power boards!"}
{"Author": "Arden Larberg", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Every time the stupid app disconnects my plugs all turn off. Thank goodness I ended up not using them on anything important."}
{"Author": "cs29email", "Date": "September 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It sucks. Bought it so i can schedule when the lights go off and on while out on vacation but the timer setting wont work. Also, Now when i go on vacation, i cant even manually turn on and off the lighting. The app doesnt recognize the device while we are away. And yes i have the Remote Access turned on."}
{"Author": "P Arango", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works maybe 60% of the time. Even when it finds devices, it can't reliably turn them on or off.  Update: they added a widget so you can control devices from your home screen.  It doesn't work reliably either."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Totally janky. App is absolute garbage. Read the other reviews. Schedule doesn't work, product setup is impossible, app is unsupported. I wouldn't allow the  developer of this app to make a cheese sandwich. If you're standing in a store right now trying to decide if you should buy a WeMo product based on its app reviews; DON'T BUY IT. Total junk."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The concept is good the interface is clunky and updates are very buggy. Setting up various on/ off times requires a degree in app design to follow the illogical set up. It's a step up from the basic Honeywell plug but super frustrating!"}
{"Author": "Warren Osten", "Date": "October 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Most frustrating / useless thing I have ever used. After about 10 attempts at connecting it still only barely recognises 2 out of 3 devices"}
{"Author": "Carrie Wilczewski", "Date": "September 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The setup took a little longer and had a few bugs than I anticipated. Once I finally got that to work it worked fine for turning lights on and off with Alexa, UNTIL I set up a rule while I was on vacation. When I got back, I disabled the rule to stop the lights automatically turning on and off in the app BUT every single day since I \"disabled\" the rule it still turns my lights on and off according the to times set in the rule! It's so frustrating and there's no way to fix this. I tried unplugging and replugging to no avail. You need to get these bugs fixed asap!"}
{"Author": "Joseph Munster", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Never works.  Won't upgrade firmware.  Great idea but horrible execution.  Hate that I already committed to several switches or I would just toss and replace.  Don't waste time or money on this junk."}
{"Author": "Song Chen", "Date": "September 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worst ux designed, slow ui and now it crashes all the time upon launching. Tplink's kasa is much better."}
{"Author": "Toua Xiong", "Date": "October 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Used to work... Now it has issues try to turn off/on devices.  Sometimes it will work for one click.  Most of the time not.  The rules are also no existent now as the link does not work."}
{"Author": "Paul Nelson", "Date": "October 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Initial install was fine. Then, I had to change router and modem.  Can't get the unit to recognize new equipment.  Software has been installed and reinstalled and it now freezes.  Very poor instructions and support."}
{"Author": "Isai Damier", "Date": "October 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "What a piece of junk this app is! You cannot connect because I change my wifi provider! Give me a place to change it in the app"}
{"Author": "AAA 3", "Date": "October 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Received the wemo bulbs for free from a wireless company. Wemo bulb functionality is down right frustrating. Horrible user interface - hardly intuitive. Bulb settings (rules) are not followed...lights go on when they want; if they go on at all. I'm going back to standard bulbs and tossing this in the trash."}
{"Author": "Blake Graham", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Terrible mess.  Was 4 stars because of load times. Now the load times are worse when it works at all. Also, for no apparent reason, remote access stopped working (no, I didn't change anything on my router) which broke IFTTT. I wanted to love wemo, but it's a buggy mess. I've transitioned to Philips hue"}
{"Author": "Craig T", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Nice work, just make the outlet smaller.  Edit: This outlet stopped working after 1 month. It won't connect to my WiFi any more. Reset to factory default and no change. Contacted Belkin and they replace the device, but the new one has the same issue! Tried reinstalling the app and clearing cached data. My WiFi works on 10 other devices without issue everyday. Too bad this thing isn't flat otherwise I could use as a coaster. Have to pay return shipping on my old one to top it off."}
{"Author": "Nicholas Twort", "Date": "September 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App crashes on launch when wifi connected. Used to work until the latest update. On LTE the app appears to launch. OnePlus 3T"}
{"Author": "Marc Armstead", "Date": "August 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "You earned the 5 stars.  Everything works great. One of the most reliable and smoothest working home automation apps out there. Went from worst to first! Keep it up. I love the device."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "As soon as my device has been in standby I have to manually kill the app each time I want to control my lights. This is happening on 3 different android devices."}
{"Author": "David Kirby", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Need support for multiple locations... This can easily be done if a username/password and/or trusted device system is implemented by Belkin. If it doesn't come soon, I'm looking for new smart home devices."}
{"Author": "Thad Tucker", "Date": "August 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app is necessary for setting up your lights the first time. Beyond that it's pointless and it doesn't work most of the time.  Controlling your WeMo devices with Google home works perfectly."}
{"Author": "Stuart Redrup", "Date": "September 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worst product ever, out of the box it worked fine. Soon as you update firmware and the app nothing but trouble. Nothing will sync correctly, no idea on system settings, link bridge reports pairing but nothing shows up and rules only work in current session and don't save.  Would not recommend to a friend. Considering the switch to z-wave. No lost to me as I got these wemo products as part of a prize bundle."}
{"Author": "Chinook Skier", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I watched a youtube movie and had my two switches going in five minutes. Belkin has a very good name and the support is excellent when I had a question, I highly recommend this product, it let's me restart my remote surveillance cameras when they lock up. These plugs work perfect."}
{"Author": "Brandon Wilson", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Setting up rules for multiple devices DOES NOT work. App is poorly made.  Clunky interface."}
{"Author": "Ewen Bell", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Really disappointing that after all these years they still haven't got this app working properly. Buggy. Prone to locking up. Setup is needlessly painful and slow. The only thing less impressive than this app is the Wemo widget... and the response from tech support when I tried to get these issues resolved. Don't expect much from this app."}
{"Author": "Eric Prengel", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Quite simple to set up and work well.  Delays in loading can happen as well as issues connecting the plugs during initial setup.  Just reload app and all is well.  Great product."}
{"Author": "Will Jenkins", "Date": "September 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Both of my \"smart\" plugs disconnect daily. It's a hassle to unplug them, plug them back in and wait for them to reconnect."}
{"Author": "Rick Katz", "Date": "September 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Horrible! I own a multitude of smart devices and Belkin Wemo is just junk. My cheap Chinese smartplugs ($10 ea.) are immensely superior. Don't buy this junk."}
{"Author": "Jason Michael Blair", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Needlessly complex to register a simple outlet. Set up is impossible to figure out. Nothing connects. App Endlessly crashing. Can't set up anything.  Troubleshooting is no help.  No further instruction, action or guidance after that.  Massive disappointment and waste of money."}
{"Author": "Jim Kottas", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app restarts itself a few times a minute, switching between WiFi and cellular. I don't see why a poor WiFi connection is a fatal error."}
{"Author": "Stephen Wetterlund", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Unreliable - when it works, it's a great app and quality smart plug in. difficult to program and setup though the instructions are great. both the app and the plug seem buggy. usually have to reinstall the app, reset plugs and reset schedules for pwr disruptions, router changes/outages."}
{"Author": "John Bennett", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The more I use it, the worse it gets! 2 main questions: WHY do 3rd party apps work so much better than the Wemo app : AND WHY does it work better when you turn off local WiFi, and use 3/4G? Don't believe they are trying.  Few problems setting up... But all good now. Has changed to pathetic. Bought some bulbs and now nothing is working. Pretty unreliable.... I really WANT to like it..."}
{"Author": "Martha Cannary", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Fails to update. Also fails with IFTTT. Software is not very intuitive. Such promise. Such a let down. One star."}
{"Author": "Portia Gardner", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Well it was working fine until the update, now it's not.  I can hear the clicking sound of the switch h trying to turn on, but the light doesn't come on."}
{"Author": "Mike's World", "Date": "August 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Udated: Does this last update actually support ALL WeMo devices, or only the ones connected to just one of your networks?     Why would you.limit sales by not allowing users to install WeMo devices at other locations, like the cabin or the office?   Hard to believe, but if you want to use a WeMo switch at a different location than home, i.e. at work or at the cabin, you will have to buy a new phone for each location.  Your programmer is keeping WeMo from becoming a great product and app."}
{"Author": "Susan Towsley", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I was so excited to install this.  Then I discovered that I have to be home to use it?  Totally useless!"}
{"Author": "Jason Reid", "Date": "September 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Tremendously slow to use, minimal lack of control through settings. Outlet can be hobbled by lack of firmware update, you just need to wait for it to present itself. I visited a different time zone months ago, it automatically changed my time settings and I still see no way to correct it."}
{"Author": "D B", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It didn't work well back in early 2017 becuz too many bugs within the app..but now it works so well..love this app now. Works really well with Amazon echo Alexa!!"}
{"Author": "Igor Kurylak", "Date": "October 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App has some bugs and performance issue. After update on every device, app shows infinite update process-needs to reinstall the app. After update works Great!"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "October 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app now freezes and won't let me make any changes. You're better than this WeMo, please fix. Otherwise a great product."}
{"Author": "Santiago Montano", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Update (9/11/17) - I was mistaken. I cant control my Mini over my VPN, even though Im connected to my LAN. Dissapointing. The official Philips Hue app supports this functionality. I dont see why this couldnt work the same. Ill keep trying, but if I cant find a solution to remotely controlling the plug over my VPN, Ill have to return the device. Major bummer.  Just got this (9/9/17.) So far so good, this wemo MINI is everything Ive been looking for: 1. A connected outlet, providing simple on/off control from my phone/tablet devices. 2. It HAD to be accessible from the internet, NOT through a wemo account/servers, but instead over my own VPN connection to my LAN. 3. An app with reasonable permissions, that I can deny on a per-feature basis, without breaking the app. 4. Finally, I need it to be reliable. (Manual control of firmware updates should contribute to that, but Id like to see a detailed change log displayed when they are offered.) This wemo device and app are, so far, on par with my Hue lights for function, ease of use, and flexibility. If this continues to hold true, I can see more wemo devices in my future. wemo, so far, is a pleasant surprise, in a world of over reaching, flaky, and consumer-hostile software, hardware, and services."}
{"Author": "Robert Aldaco", "Date": "October 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Cannot change to a new wifi Network and support pages are useless. I have 7 switches and light switches. Takes hours to change to new wifi if you can get them to change."}
{"Author": "Steven Kline", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Inconsistencies in the operation. Upgrades to devices doesn't seem to work all of the time"}
{"Author": "Paul Heller", "Date": "August 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Great, when it works. Not very reliable, all the devices have about a 50% chance of showing up. Hardly see all 4 of mine connected at the same time."}
{"Author": "Nev C", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Belkin stuff seems to be pretty unstable and incomsistent despite nice packaging and aesthics/form factor... Shame really. A sleep function on WeMo app wouldn't go a miss either!"}
{"Author": "Jeff Jones", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App gets confused easily requiring power cycling of the wemo device and restart of the app.  Initial Setup was problematic too."}
{"Author": "Benjamin Pfeiffer", "Date": "August 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not great app fails to connect need to restart app constantly.  I will be going to a better product Update has failed for the last month to download"}
{"Author": "Peter Warren", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Super inconsistent. Have to regularly reinstall the app. Often rules spontaneously stop working."}
{"Author": "Darragh Jones", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Great when it works but firmware never installs properly and system hangs. Just changed my broadband provider and painful trying to get it reconnected."}
{"Author": "XS Orsburn", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Disappointed. After reading positive reviews decided to try this instead of a cheaper switch from a competitor unfortunately the WeMo is inferior.  This app is terrible. possibly the most buggy Android app I've ever used in many years of Android use . I purchased 2 mini smart plug devices and neither of them have worked consistently since the day I set them up. One works from time to time the other shows \"not available\" even after multiple attempts to reset the device. This app is awful and takes multiple minutes to load simple commands. I am running on Android 8.0 with Nexus 6p so I don't believe my phone is the problem. I hope you can update this sad app or I will be returning the product very soon."}
{"Author": "Abhinay Mukunthan", "Date": "August 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The rules are extremely inconsistent. Each time I open the app, the rules disappear! The device also often disappears on the LAN. A great idea let down by an atrocious app."}
{"Author": "Hanz Raudge", "Date": "September 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The only gripe I have is when the app is launched, it takes a while to locate and detect the WeMo device. Does it have to \"locate\" it every time?!?  Besides that, I'm happy with the improved version, as the earlier one was quite buggy, which is why I stopped using it and the WeMo plug was sitting in my drawer until this newer version came out and I got it back into service."}
{"Author": "Gordon Garradd", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Intial device connection is problematic and I've had to attempt it several times before succeeding with each of my 2 switches, but they have worked perfectly well since then.  Firmware updates have not caused me any problems, although they seem to hang in \"updating\" until I refresh to discover they are complete. I'm using them to control pumps and backup battery chargers in aquaponics systems, where I need complex timing programs which aren't doable with regular mechanical or electronic timers. They have been completely reliable for over a month now."}
{"Author": "Tate F", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Using this is very clumsy, software takes ages to find devices, and there is a sizeable delay between app command and power on at least half of the time. However, the scheduling works very well! It's frustrating, because it's great when it works, but it seems like a lottery determines when that is."}
{"Author": "Carl M", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Understanding the app is ridiculously hard! I have few problems understanding apps usually but this app is totally flawed &amp; needs a re-make. What were they thinking?"}
{"Author": "Daniel Machado", "Date": "September 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "JUNK! DO NOT BUY THIS PRODUCT! Works 10% of the time. It's been 4 years and no progress.  Updates get worse every time. I am so disappointed in Belkin. Don't think I will by another BELKIN PRODUCT."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Wemo is NOT user friendly - you have to jump through a ton of hoops that other smart products dont require.  I would highly recommend staying away from Wemo products!"}
{"Author": "Daniel Gonsoulin", "Date": "August 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Instructions are useless. Hope you know something about networking!!"}
{"Author": "Justin Hendrix", "Date": "September 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not a smooth setup adding devices like the tutorial says, hit or miss getting it to work. Took several tries repeating the steps before it add a wemo smart outlet"}
{"Author": "Josh Venie", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Occasionally loses connection to devices, but overall I'd say about 98% reliable on the first try. Would like to see widgets from Belkin for faster switching as 3rd party widgets are unreliable."}
{"Author": "Landon Philip", "Date": "September 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "For me.. If I manually turn on switch app freezes and won't let me turn off switch. Google home operates it better."}
{"Author": "Sameer Sheth", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Very sluggish app, take forever to do anything even though I own an OnePlus 5 phone , which has 8 GB RAM.   WeMo device switch does not show up and after numerous reset / restart it final show in this app. Even after finally showing up it's very difficult to set up rules such as Switch on at sunset or switch off after an hour, etc... Painful app and hardware"}
{"Author": "Andrew McGinnis", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Overall, it works ok. It's weakness is that it fails to recognize a light that's been turned on (or on then off) since  the last time you used the Wemo app. You have to switch the light manually before Wemo can \"see\" it, then you must close the app and start it again before it will let you adjust the lighting. In short, it's great if you ALWAYS use the app, but a pain in the ads if you dare operate the light manually."}
{"Author": "Carol Phillips", "Date": "October 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Won't stay connected. All other WiFi devices function properly. Updates of firmware, reinstallation, nothing keeps Wemo connected.  Quite useless waste of money."}
{"Author": "Stanley Paez", "Date": "September 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worked for a while but after a power outtage, the devices disappeared from the Wemo app. Also, I found using the devices through Wi-Fi was more reliable than through Cellular connections.  Where is the consistency and reliability??"}
{"Author": "Ian McLean", "Date": "August 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Slow unresponsive, poor support, difficult to set up. On Android 7 there are problems, but on Android 8 Nexus 5x it had become completely unusable. Reports incorrect status of lights, killing and restarting app does not fix."}
{"Author": "Todd Gregory", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I'm a pretty smart and techie guy. I managed a computer lab for several years so I'm a trouble shooting pro. Can't get these to work consistently."}
{"Author": "Michael Perea", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The link has to be reset if you change routers or your wifi password. Then it's a huge pain to get it recognized by the app and back onto the network. You have to setup bulbs again too. It's also not one of the wemo products supported by Amazon Echo a d you have to use ifttt"}
{"Author": "Jonathon Lee", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Majority of the time the app works. Sometimes has false readings if something is on or off. Force stopping the app and opening it back up resolves the issue"}
{"Author": "Enrique E. de Orta", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Newer versions have been getting more reliable..summer time changes keep messing my schedules though. Needed to recreate them to fix it."}
{"Author": "Paul Jarolimekproner", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I like the dimmers , the app on the other hand feels pretty buggy. Constant disconnect and crashes"}
{"Author": "Alex L", "Date": "August 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I used to have this rated at one star, bit it's gotten a lot better. Belkin is slow but consistent in fixing issues and making this more stable, and they're now at the point where I can call it good and recommend it to non-tech enthusiasts. If you want to make rules for electronics and don't mind going through setup 3 times when it fails the first two, wemo is amazing. Once you have everything setup the way you want....in the word of Steve Jobs, it just works. IFTTT integration is good too."}
{"Author": "Rick Gioia", "Date": "October 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The App is slow on my LGv20. It had a hard time finding the device. Finally worked but trying on/off scheduling  rules would just  get constant spinning circle. I also couldn't add location for dusk to Dawn functionality. I hate to say it, because I hate Apple, I tried my Wife's iPhone and it worked flawlessly."}
{"Author": "Richard Carlson", "Date": "October 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works fairly well.  Some rules are hard to use"}
{"Author": "Felipe Pubillones", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Tends to lose connection to one switch over WiFi, but not cellular. Latest update has made my rules disappea, yet somehow still function. Overall still a hot mess. I'm using my old plugs now at the apartment I'm in for med school, but at my aunt's house I already switched everything from WeMo to Z-wave. If you want home automation, don't even look at WeMo. It's beyond being the worst platform."}
{"Author": "Kris Arnott", "Date": "October 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The WeMo devices work very nicely and I am impressed.  I have an issue with how the application shows me a loading screen, then it shows me a connecting to network screen, then it shows me the devices if they are detected, (they fail about 20% of the time) then it has to refresh the status on all devices. This means if i want to turn on the light for a room with my device i have to wait somewhere from 20 sec to 2 min to flip a light switch.  You need to cache this data and refresh it in the background, and use push messages on status changes for updates.  The app is also lacking widgets for the home screen, a fast easy way to toggle devices is critical for ease of use.  There is also a problem that the application times out frequently when creating rules or the failing to save a rule."}
{"Author": "Backroads", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Device setup is easy, but the app is glitchy.  Sometimes toggling a switch won't get the desired action, sometimes the device disappears from the app for a time."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works well, use it to remotely restart my security cameras when they go off line.  Great product. ."}
{"Author": "peter lys", "Date": "September 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Very finicky. Help pages are weak. Direct user support is good."}
{"Author": "Steve Dyer", "Date": "August 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Doesn't connect half the time. Constantly have to unplug and plug in the wemo block. Lights only dim through control some of the time. Very disappointed :/"}
{"Author": "Frank Woll", "Date": "September 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Everyone there is an update to firmwaste, because it certainly isn't firmware, I spend hours testing everything and maybe it works..maybe it doesn't. Latest firm ware didn't allow me to save rules on wifi.. But does save the rule when connected by cellular.. Even with rule saved devices don't notice the rule and stay on. I'm finally throwing all 4 of my insights into the trash..."}
{"Author": "THE DON", "Date": "October 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "These work very well. Needs to have more of a security feature to prevent others from mischievous stunts. Do love it. Thanks."}
{"Author": "Ted Naemura", "Date": "September 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app updated itself straightaway, which added to setup time, but worked as intended after first setup attempt.  We like it very well!"}
{"Author": "Aaron Robles", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works fine just remember your devices that contorl the wemo need to be on 2.4ghz wifi. 5ghz isn't supported. Learned that the hard way with my Google Home."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Problems with app dropping out and needing resetting, until I obtained better modem. Several flawless months now!"}
{"Author": "Justin Villanueva", "Date": "August 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Mr. Coffee WeMo smart coffee maker does not play well with Samsung Connect Home Pro. Even after following all setup instructions, I had to change SSID of an old router to match my current  home network's SSID just to get the WeMo device to work on the network. WeMo needs to work on making setup simple."}
{"Author": "IHM plumbing", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Amazing experience. We have over 11 units all over my home and it's made life easier for us . This app totally works like it's made to ..... Great with Alexa"}
{"Author": "Jeff Wu", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can not find More button even all user manuals refer to one for firmware upgrade.   Very poor QA, at least Android version. Updated: just got TPLink Switch.  It's Kasa app way better than Wemo app.  IPhone version of Wemo app is better.  However, the Android version still much room to improve stability and reliability."}
{"Author": "Jason Silva", "Date": "August 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "New update says wemo cloud service is offline and that i can control my devices by lan... yet i am on my lan and i cant do anything! What the hell! Do yyou guys even test releases?"}
{"Author": "Todd Bradley", "Date": "August 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "When it works, it's GREAT. Nice not needing some hub... quite 'glitchy' though; I'm pretty 'techie and Wemo can stress me out at times."}
{"Author": "Amber Barnes", "Date": "September 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "So many bugs. Got the device earlier this year and have had nearly constant troubles. If one device turns it on, that device must turn it off. Most of the time. Once in a while it has to be a different device that turns it off... So have to be weary of turning it on because you may not be able to turn it off. Such a mess."}
{"Author": "Jules Saunderson", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Barely works. Always wants you to reconnect to already connected devices. The only workaround appears to be to reset all the devices and reconnect them... The products work well, but the app is garbage."}
{"Author": "Ken Daniels", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "/span> I see this app is still being worked on and yet still no widgets. Why does belkin hate widgets?"}
{"Author": "Dirk Hall", "Date": "August 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Love this!!  This is a genius system that is incredibly user friendly and convenient!  The ability to customize brew times for a full week ahead of time.  Also if I'm headed home and want a cup of coffee I simply tap the brew button and hot coffee is waiting when I arrive!  In addition the system is beautifully designed!!  A++"}
{"Author": "Justin Kozak", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "set up the switch successfully.. but app then refuses to find any devices"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Memo insight unrecognizable by Wi-Fi. App default to idiot screens with useless configuration info. This app get worse with each update."}
{"Author": "Charlie Roberts", "Date": "September 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have had this app for 6 months.  Seems to work well with multiple devices. Not the most intuitive, and more rule options would be nice."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App is total garbage. Installed a wemo switch and attempted to set up the device on my network via the app.  App would repeatedly hang during various stages of the setup. Wasted about 2 hrs and device is still not fully configured.  Will be returning the switch and uninstalling the app."}
{"Author": "Jared Piatt", "Date": "October 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Barely Functional. Setting timers is tedious. Really I can't just type in a time?? UI is cryptic, setup is slow and buggy. Had a smart plug over a year. Works fine, just try not to touch the app... Samsung smart things and Alexa can control the switch. I use it mostly for a basic timer. Sunset Sunrise settings make the app lock up. (Pixel XL 7.2.0 and Note 8 7.1.0) ...This was a gift or I would have returned it for a Zwave plug... oh by the way the whole system falls on its face without wifi the timer even stops working mine won't work on 5gz either... I'd give you a %50 chance of having good luck with this... Belkin I expected more from your brand..."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Set up takes ages and does not always work first time. When i go to check the hardware information a spinner appears then nothing happens. Please fix."}
{"Author": "Hamish Robinson", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Slow to start and then slow to find devices, warning to devs, the Xiaomi Mi Home app causes your wemo app to instant crash on startup on WiFi, problem went away after uninstalling Mi Home app then wemo worked fine"}
{"Author": "Joshua Mazess", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Still very buggy. Hit or miss with finding devices, and firmware updates usually fail, often several times. Why is there no retry option or a way to push an update from the app to the device?"}
{"Author": "Brandon Randle", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "There's a bug on the \"export data\" page for Insight Switches where the Email Address box keeps resetting as you're typing so you can only type half of your email address. It's been like this for 3 months, can you fix it?"}
{"Author": "Cl\u00e9ment Hazan", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Quand je change les r\u00e8gles, les nouveaux param\u00e8tres ne sont pas pris en compte et reviennent toujours \u00e0 de anciennes r\u00e8gles enregistr\u00e9es avant .. Impossible d'utiliser les lampes correctement :("}
{"Author": "Jules Bullock", "Date": "September 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have 2 heaters. I can't set up a daily schedule on 1, let alone add the 2nd heater to the app. The heater won't maintain a set temp, it's constantly bouncing from 21 to 24\u00b0C. Do not recommend."}
{"Author": "Shu Yang", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Devices work well but the app had crashed so many times and never completely finished update. I also had to uninstall and install the app multiple times for it to detect all devices."}
{"Author": "Ryan Kukla", "Date": "October 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Again this app is stupid for android and I had to use an iPhone to setup my devices since I switched to a new router. Belkin please get it together and figure this issue out."}
{"Author": "Erin DeLavan", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I used to love this app, but since the most recent update the lights have been real buggy and have not been turning on when they're supposed to or turning off at random times and it's been real frustrating. I've tried resetting the devices and it hasn't fixed the problem."}
{"Author": "Gabriel Escamilla", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app sucks I've been trying to update firmware on my light switches and is being 'downloading' the firmware forever. I can't remove the switches from the app and re-join them I tried to reset them but got same message. Reinstall does nothing... Useless"}
{"Author": "Dan", "Date": "August 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not once in two years have I been able to create or save any rules, even after the latest update!  I use Muzzley app, works every time."}
{"Author": "Lavonna Schank", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It does not work with the crock pot. I've came home multiple times to no food cooked.  Tried calling and get people who barely speak English.  Worthless for a busy mom."}
{"Author": "Lee Toll", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Liked this app and device a lot more before the update.  I go to swipe and it's gone, reopen, swipe,  gone.  Getting irritated.  Loved it before."}
{"Author": "Anthony Wong", "Date": "October 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Doesn't work at all. Only using widget button can turn on and off devices. App is stuck saying the devices are \"downloading an update\" and therefore non responsive. I cannot even remove the devices. Can't wipe them and factory reset."}
{"Author": "Graeme Durie", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is literally the worst app I've ever come across. It doesn't ever find the switches, try Domi from the windows store, written by a 10 year old, works every time."}
{"Author": "Odell Jones Jr", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app does not always work.  It requires constantly uninstalling and reinstalling.  I've got 2 lights, 2 light switches and 1 wemo maker.  Primarily, it's the lights that are the worst.  In/off doesn't work well, can't dim them much or change the color time."}
{"Author": "Sasha Zbrozek", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App is clunky and slow, but can be made to work. The home screen widget are super unreliable garbage. I regret buying this hardware and am going to return it."}
{"Author": "T Noonan", "Date": "September 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It has somehow gotten worse. Who is performing their development &amp; maintenance?"}
{"Author": "Chris Husband", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's barely ok. The Wemos are great. It's this app that is terrible"}
{"Author": "John Legge", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Your app sucks. Never is reliable. Have a new switch that it can't connect to; even though it's less than five feet from the router. What a waste of time and money!"}
{"Author": "David Mackenzie", "Date": "October 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Plugs keep dropping out and showing as not connected.  Have to reset them and then reinstall. Can still control through Alex's so must be a problem with the app."}
{"Author": "Jacob Scutaru", "Date": "August 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's a pain to set up, and sucks at remembering WiFi. When it works it's fine, just can't move or reset your router. And now it's not remembering scheduled either. Oh and it never actually upgrades."}
{"Author": "Matt Keith", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "U guys need to add a button to notifications bar so u don't have to exit what ur doing to go into app or use the widget"}
{"Author": "Luis Mercado", "Date": "September 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "For some reason when I'm not home it connects fine to my wemo switches on 4g network,  but when i get home connected on my wifi,  don't connect to my devices ,,and sometimes it does the same thing but the other way around connects to wifi but don't connect to 4g ..."}
{"Author": "Richard Booth", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "4* on iOS 0* on Android.  Lacks advertised functionality (Sunrise-sunset for example).  Setting rules entirely non-intuitive.  If I hadn't had my old iPhone, I woulda returned my switch for a Lutron."}
{"Author": "Peter Mortensen", "Date": "October 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Ok, but I can't save any rules to the device. Despite being able to use the device through the WeMo app, when I try and save or delete a rule, the app tells me the device is not connected and refuses to make changes."}
{"Author": "Jax McCaughan", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "No easy way to reset devices or correct password typo. Had to uninstall and reinstall 3 times to get devices 2 simple  working again"}
{"Author": "Kate Fletcher", "Date": "October 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app isn't very user friendly. With every refresh it seems to lose the rules I have saved. Why are there SO MANY firmware updates?"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "August 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Sometimes products works well, however if there is an update or something changes, it's the worst product ever and system goes down for several days or weeks"}
{"Author": "Terry G", "Date": "August 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The on/off works well. So does the Alexa integration. However the programming for vacation mode, ie turning on and off at  random times is confusing and not user friendly."}
{"Author": "Sharon Green", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not working with Google Home. I set up wemo through Google Home app and through ifttt, it used to work but doesn't work anymore. I have a wemo socket which  still works through Alexa but when I ask Google to turn my TV on and off nothing happens anymore."}
{"Author": "Cynthia Johnson", "Date": "October 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "A virus tried to load while installing app, otherwise app working correctly. Update takes a long time."}
{"Author": "Michael Lee", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Horrible system and app.  Did they even test this before it was released.  Do not buy. I have never been able to control wemo devices from the app"}
{"Author": "David van Spankeren", "Date": "September 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app shows me an average usage of a few minutes a day and average monthly costs of around 0.50\u20ac. I wish it was true but I use my switch with all my a/v equipment attached for an average of 8 hours a day so it doesn't monitor the usage/cost correctly! So all it does is turn on/off remotely and for that there are cheaper options on the market!"}
{"Author": "Leon Janzen", "Date": "September 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The device is slow when getting it connected to WiFi, but it seems to be reliable so far; the app works well, and I really like the power monitoring features of the Insight plug."}
{"Author": "Herman Sykes", "Date": "October 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Really have not had any issues with this app or the wemo products.  Use it with two switches, two dimmer switches, and two outlet switches.  My wife loves them so happy wife happy life!"}
{"Author": "Cullen Kawano", "Date": "August 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Recently have had issues with trying to schedule a switch. It constantly says device not found. Tried a full reset and now it won't connect to anything..."}
{"Author": "Michele Wagner", "Date": "September 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Finally I don't have to worry about running around the house to turn lights off. We had X10 but it never quite got all the lights. This has not missed a single Scheduled event."}
{"Author": "Stanford Paul", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Horrible to setup.  If it wasn't already wired in I would either return it or throw it in the garbage."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App takes a long time to open.  Also, my light is rarely detected by the app so I can't use it once it does open."}
{"Author": "Bill Moser", "Date": "October 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Lots of problems getting connected &amp; working. After about 10 attempts got it to work. Then it did a FW update and stopped working again. Yay!"}
{"Author": "Lori P", "Date": "August 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app is very clunky and the recent update erased all of my existing rules. Away mode has never worked"}
