"Kevo"
{"Author": "Bradley Wuthrich", "Date": "September 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The privacy policy us almost as bad as Schlage's. Like most corporations they share with their partners which makes sense; however, how that information is protected and used beyond them is unspecified and not protected by the privacy policy. I would prefer apps and devices independent of GPS tracking, cloud based services, and data collection.  They should work independently of their creators. I like IP enabled devices that can be managed outside of their creators. I would be more comfortable with Quickset if they offered an app and device that did not collect or connect online. Just solely Bluetooth &amp; NFC"}
{"Author": "Stephen Thompson", "Date": "September 30, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app has been working great since February 2017 but since the last couple of updates it doesn't work properly in any consistent way. I'm using a Samsung Galaxy S7 on Android 6.1 and its reliability has dropped to such a low point that I now need to carry physical keys with me because it only works less than 40% of the time. Sometimes I log off and back on the app works and sometimes it doesn't. I'm having the same issue on a second phone an iPhone 6. These are both Kevo 1st generation deadbolts.  Same issue with both locks."}
{"Author": "jeff strong", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have a Galaxy S8 plus. The app used to work fine on my phone until the most recent update in September 2017 and now it hasn't worked since. I feel like I've been scammed on a $230 lock that I now have to carry a key with me all the time. TiVo needs to step up their game quickly! This is baloney"}
{"Author": "mauricio santiago", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Note 8, no app support. Based on other user reviews, apparently most android phones aren't supported. Prior to my note 8 my moto z would constantly stop working or reading the kevo, same with a pixel. It's apparent android isnt supported by kevo, but if so it should not be marketed as such... save me the headache and I would not have purchased!! Anyone reading this, don't buy (assuming you dont have an iPhone, because why would you be in the play store?)"}
{"Author": "Evan Labbe", "Date": "October 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The touch lock works when it feels like it. I carry a physical key around at all times since its on a business.   Setup is simple, easy to manage, battery life is ok.   But phone support also seems to be an issue. My brothers galaxy s8 seems to work, but my note 8 doesn't. All of our other phones are supported, but how well they work is hit or miss. My IPhone 6, fails almost every time. The iPhone 7 works well, and my old note 4 works every single time.   It's a terribly frustrating system from a reliability standpoint."}
{"Author": "Tyler Beckett", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "And back to not supporting my phone. I just picked up the Essential PH-1 and this app does not work despite having Bluetooth LE. Can only manually unlock in the app, cannot unlock using the phone as a key."}
{"Author": "Sean Conroy", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Great on my s6 edge plus but now on my Note 8 it's not supported. So now it's useless! Not sure why it takes KEVO so long to send updates for Android phones! Don't buy if you have a newer Android device!!!!"}
{"Author": "dragon788", "Date": "October 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Friend wanted me to stop by and pick up something from his place, \"get the Kevo app and it'll let you unlock the door\" he said. I signed up for an account, logged in and got the guest eKEY he sent me, went to his place and couldn't unlock the door with either of my phones. One is on the supported list and the other is new enough to have all the Bluetooth features required, yet neither works. Guess I won't be buying any for my own home."}
{"Author": "Sean Bello", "Date": "October 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Response time has been awful with Oreo. It takes multiple tries to lock or unlock, taking away it's convenience. Having a piece of tech that doesn't work correctly is embarrassing, so getting a better product."}
{"Author": "Brooke B.", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I am getting a \"unknown location\" every time I log on to app. Where it lets you unlock the front door from app. My boyfriend has the app. And has a galaxy 6 and his can unlock the door from app. And it shows the location. I have the galaxy 8 and I can't. PLEASE FIX this for us galaxy 8's!!!! Other than that love the app.  Very handy when you don't feel like digging for keys in purse :)"}
{"Author": "Sammn Maillet", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Had trouble on my S8+, wont even work with my Note 8. please fix, really sucks not being able to get in my front door."}
{"Author": "Robin Rehberg", "Date": "September 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "They are too slow making updates and supporting devices. Lost use of it after Oreo update.  Simple Bluetooth app, shouldn't be that complicated."}
{"Author": "Rob Brawders", "Date": "September 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This lock has come a long way. The latest updates really have improved the range and consistency with which is detects devices, and has eliminated most of the lag between when you touch your Kevo and when it actually unlocks. Not quite ready for prime-time yet, still a little flaky and will leave you standing at your door touching the lock wondering why it's not locking/unlocking every couple of times you to go use it. Fobs.. those still seem to be something of a dumpster fire. But hey, at least with the app on your phone things are improving!"}
{"Author": "Juan hernandez", "Date": "October 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have the gateway and its annoying that it asks to turn on the Bluetooth every dam time. Also fails to communicate."}
{"Author": "Kelly Lane", "Date": "September 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app is junk, so is the hardware. Do not waste your time or money"}
{"Author": "Kenneth Foggie", "Date": "October 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The Samsung Galaxy Note 8 has been out for almost a month now and I'm still getting unsupported device errors. $229 for this horrible support"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Improved, starting to get there. Not fully supporting Android Oreo yet, disappointing."}
{"Author": "Chris G", "Date": "October 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Android supported my ass. Dont sell a product claiming its android capable when infact it only supports like two types of phones. Not sure why the phone matters when its the software that should! I have a LG G4 and right upon installation, I basically cant do ANYTHING with the app that would give me access to the door by any means. Dont waste your money on this hyped up doorlock and go back to the manual ways. Kwikset/KEVO you should be embarassed with this product and the support it doesnt even provide. Read the reviews people! It doesnt work unless you own a google phone or only a Galaxy series phone..someone must be making good money off that."}
{"Author": "John Puhoff", "Date": "September 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Love the program but after android wear 2.0 update the app crashes on smart watch can u guys fix it? Thanks"}
{"Author": "Jacky Feng", "Date": "September 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Recently I got issue unlock my Kevo with my phone. I have to carry physical key with me because very often I need to use the physical key to open the door after standing outside my door for minutes with several failed touch-to-unlock with my phone. Bad product."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "September 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app doesn't work with a Sony phone. Very disappointing. The lock works with my Samsung and my daughters iPhone but not my husbands Sony.  I am in Australia and we can't get Kevo Plus either.  If I had known all this before forking out $300 I would have bought the Samsung lock.  I can't even get a response from Kevo support regarding Kevo plus."}
{"Author": "Chris Smithson", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can never register my kevo first gen. It generates an ekey, and then tells me there is no internet connection, over wifi or cellular lte..."}
{"Author": "Abe lincoln", "Date": "September 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It randomly updates and does not up dat flagship devices. Making the non compliant and in usable . epic fail."}
{"Author": "Chris Cecil", "Date": "September 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Please enable for Galaxy Note 8. Says device not supported when launched."}
