{"Author": "Ricardo Morales", "Date": "October 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works perfectly"}
{"Author": "Richard Lillie", "Date": "October 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Love the concept"}
{"Author": "Greg L", "Date": "May 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app has come a long way. The lock/unlock signal travels much faster now. The low battery notification is nice as well. Only thing i wojld syggest is a manual refresh button yo see if the deadbolt is locked right this moment. It nirmally refreshes at a certain interval. 5min?"}
{"Author": "ToMMy BoY", "Date": "June 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Installation was easy, and the setup was painless. When I downloaded the app, it initially stated that my Galaxy S6 Active wasn't compatible, but I was still able to calibrate both it and my key fob with no problems. The software update downloaded and installed successfully as well. Now I love my new door lock. Just don't keep your key fob anywhere close to the lock, and you won't have any issues to deal with."}
{"Author": "William Hart", "Date": "July 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Garbage. Takes too long too access the lock so I'm standing in front of my door waiting for my phone to pair. The people I send a key to have to dowbload the app and make an account to use the key... How annoying.   I'm returning my lock and going with a Yale keyless entry model that ive used before with far greater success.   Final words, great idea, terrible execution."}
{"Author": "silox x", "Date": "May 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I had high hopes for this app since I purchased my Kevo lock (which I love).  Unfortunately the app says my phone isn't fully supported and I cannot use the touch to unlock feature or ekeys which is what I was interested in.  The problem is my phone is a Samsung Galaxy S5 which is supported and I use other BLE/BT4 devices such as the tracking tags named 'Tile'.  Not sure why my phone is not detected properly, I would really like to use this app and give it a great rating.  If anyone knows of a way to resolve this lemme know, I'd appreciate it!"}
{"Author": "Chris H", "Date": "September 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "When I first installed it. It linked up right away. Then within 5mins, would not find it again. It just Continues to search until it times out. I reset and linked it again. It worked fine for a day. Now it's back to searching.  What's the point of buying this product when I'm still going to use my keys everytime. Why do companies release buggy products that don't work. Returned. Going with schlag\u00eb"}
{"Author": "Matthew Bartlett", "Date": "May 31, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Worst designed app/lock on the market.  Why would you make a lock or app where only 2 functions work on majority of Android phones? This is just ridiculous.  The lock is a waste of money, the app doesn't work. One fob for a household and only 2 ekeys  for the cost of the lock.  That's a complete ripoff.  Plus no support in Australia. Have serious issues just connecting via Bluetooth. Waste of money and time"}
{"Author": "David Kha", "Date": "June 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Just upgraded to a 2nd Gen Kevo, and right away it works much much better than a 1st Gen Kevo. Kwikset should just recall all 1st Gens due to how unreliable it is. With a 2nd Gen Kevo the app (and fob) works almost instantaneously and reliably. A 1st Gen would always take forever and only work 30% of the time, requiring multiple retries or use of a physical key. The only issue that needs to be fixed is Android Wear 2.0 compatibility (force closes on Moto360)."}
{"Author": "Usunique L", "Date": "July 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It works on the phone with some errors, but doesn't work at all with android wear. Only an error message for that. I don't think the company try to update or improve their app so there are a lot of issues."}
{"Author": "Alaina Leighton", "Date": "September 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Slow to connect, I stood at my door for 5 minutes waiting for it to connect to unlock. Also having problems connecting with multiple devices. It's incredibly slow for all devices to unlock or lock. We have 2 Samsung Note 5's and a Samsung S7 Edge. We uninstalled the lock due to it unlocking itself. Reinstalled after we moved. Still worried it will unlock itself after I walk away like previously. Well probably try to convince husband to go with different wireless lock that's faster and less risky."}
{"Author": "james thompson", "Date": "August 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Would like to have it connect to my android wear watch at some point again.   I think this lock works great. Sure it has glitches. But for those drilling out their locks carry your dam \ud83d\udd11 too, they do supply one with the lock. Or be more patient with it"}
{"Author": "J G", "Date": "June 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Great doorlook. Works with my phone Note 4. But all features don't work with Note 3. Also wish I could check on lock remotely without having to buy the WiFi link. I gave my wife the key fob since the touch feature does not work with her Note 3"}
{"Author": "Phillip Carroll", "Date": "July 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app works well with my Weiser bluetooth lock.  My LG G6 works with touch to open feature although the app showed question marks. A call to support revealed the instructions were outdated and the tech was able to help me program the phone correctly. 4 stars because of under developed android support.  I can't get the touch to open feature to work with the LG G4 even though it is Android Marshmellow 6.0 and Bluetooth 4 compatible. 5 stars for better android support and functionality on phones that are hardware capable."}
{"Author": "Marcus Thomson", "Date": "August 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works great with my phone on Kevo 2nd gen, but still not connecting to Moto 360 via Samsung S8+. Support is non-existent as I have sent 2 emails with screenshots. They send me the same garbage that I have tried 5 different ways of uninstalling this and Android Wear with no positive results."}
{"Author": "David Hill", "Date": "August 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Had some trouble getting started. Had to use my daughter's iPhone to do initial setup which included updating lock software. Was then able to log in with my LG V20 and use the lock. Android compatibility is limited which I don't understand with 82% of phones running android os."}
{"Author": "Grant Jack", "Date": "August 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not only does this app just flat out not work properly, the product itself doesn't work properly and might be the most frustrating  home product ever created.  Unless you like approching your door, putting the kid down, your bag down, rifling around trying to find your phone, opening the app and then the door only opening 10% of the time after waiting 60 seconds for everything to sync up...this product isn't for you.  Good idea...F on execution."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "June 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It works fine.  Sometimes it gets confused and loses ability to unlock with phone.  Restarting Bluetooth on phone resolves it.  Wish it didn't do that.  Ever since android wear updated to 2.0, I can't get the app to link with watch, so can't unlock with watch anymore.  That's a bummer."}
{"Author": "Roman", "Date": "June 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Auto logout is bad. You should add option in settings to disable or enable this function.  Sometimes you just stay by the door and retype again password to close or open the door."}
{"Author": "Reggie Holder", "Date": "August 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "How can this app be limited to so few phones. Really wanted this lock but wont work. Kind of sad they don't put more effort into the app."}
{"Author": "christopher e m", "Date": "July 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have tried so hard to support Kevo, and they have made a good product. But why haven't they certified more phones after all this time? My 2014 HTC M8 wasn't supported, my 2015 M9 was lost and replaced by insurance with a 2017 LG G6 which uses the latest BLE specifications, but hasn't been certified by Kevo. This is so disappointing...I keep trying to support this product but they seem to have given up on it."}
{"Author": "cody rager", "Date": "July 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app is very minimal.  Basic functions that should be present such as seeing the lock status on the hone screen, widgets, and any customization are absent.  The honeywell connected feature is worthless since it thinks anytime a door is locked that you are away.  I wanted to like this app and with improvements it could be good, but in the current state it is way behind its competitors in terms of features"}
{"Author": "Casey Biemiller", "Date": "June 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "On newer versions of Android, you likely need to give location access permission in the settings of the app in order for the app to work. My Moto  Z Force Droid isn't listed as supported, but works just fine after I make the change. The developer needs to add a prompt for the permission so people don't have to dig in the phone's settings, but other then that, I have had no issues."}
{"Author": "Ryan Heritage", "Date": "June 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Smart phone keys don't work. Garbage Bluetooth key. Takes forever to even get it to connect just for it to fail. Totally pointless smartphone app. Should just offer more key fobs in package and lose the app."}
{"Author": "James K", "Date": "September 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My phone is Bluetooth smart (ready) but my Kevo is Bluetooth stupid. I can't even get to the install section (says it needs my location and locks up). Sure my device says it's not fully supported, great excuse for a poor app. Unfortunately too late to return this junk to the store... And after watching some YouTube videos not even sure if I want to user it as a deadbolt anyway."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "June 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Was having trouble connecting and getting an error message, once I reset the kevo device and tried connecting I was up and running! Bought this for my wife's business as she always has her hands full when arriving to work(She has the key fob) and she loves it and now so do I!"}
{"Author": "Jodaye Stuart", "Date": "June 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Won't let me see who is using the keys and when, this is the reason I bought it. The bluetooth works fine, but fix the \"history\" so I can see who is coming in going... It used to show me?... Update... Still not, showing history consistently... Crappy ap"}
{"Author": "David Hyman", "Date": "September 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I don't know what happened but the lock simply doesn't work with both the iOS and Android apps. I have reached out to their support and they are completely unresponsive"}
{"Author": "Waldemar Filipczak", "Date": "August 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not working very well on Android 6. Have to log in into my account few times a day because the app logs me out. Another thing is that you have to wait for long time before it pairs with lock (if it pairs at all !) Waste of money."}
{"Author": "Sean R", "Date": "June 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "HTC bolt, moto z force, all my device are incompatible? Update your app so I can use my lock to get in my room!"}
{"Author": "Mark Concannon", "Date": "May 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "App is consistent and works well.   Hardware/ lock has some minor issues and doesn't track physical key lock/unlock. The whole package is great, otherwise."}
{"Author": "Ur Nan", "Date": "September 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This app and product is garbage. None of my new phones work with my old locks and I'm stuck using my old phone as a key. When the app works, which is rarely, it is slow and unresponsive. Will never buy one of these sad excuses for a \"smart\" lock again."}
{"Author": "Michael Harris", "Date": "September 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Do not purchase under any circumstances. The lock is as unresponsive as the company's customer support."}
{"Author": "Nicholas Cotton", "Date": "September 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works very well with Samsung Galaxy S7 Edge. However has stopped working with Android Wear as of 2.0 - always crashes trying to configure LG Sport watch."}
{"Author": "Fred Brown", "Date": "June 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I should have read the app reviews before I bought this expensive lock. How can you only support a handful of android devices?   and Android wear support is still broken!"}
{"Author": "Aaron Wallace", "Date": "June 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works as I would expect. The instructions said it would not be compatible with my existing lock however it came with everything I needed even if I had no existing lock. The app started off a little finicky due to the verification process. Just remember to close the app after completing the verification process then opening it and starting your ekeying procedures. I use the same account on both my phone and my wife's phone so I did not have to generate another set of keys however this may cause me issues later, I guess I will find out. I love the fact that it does not connect to the Internet so it being hacked is less of a worry. Locks do not need access to the internet due to your phone being able to program them locally and you can email the ekey to someone if they need to get in without you being home. I have not tried this yet but hopefully will soon. The only issue I have at the moment is the possibility of your phone being too close to the lock while being home which can allow someone to walk up and unlock your door if your phone is too close. That can be solved by simply turning off your Bluetooth while at home but that is not something people will like to do. So far it works great with no issues."}
{"Author": "Andrew Hogg", "Date": "May 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Didn't work at all!  Created an account and every time I got a verification email it wouldn't work. Horrible and I will never own one of these ever again."}
{"Author": "Joshua Todd", "Date": "September 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have a galaxy s8+. Easy to use but not as sensitive as I would like.  My girlfriend has an iPhone 8 and the app does not run in the background so u must open the app every time. But over all the lock works great and the app is pretty easy to use."}
{"Author": "Chiu S", "Date": "July 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Installation instruction was nice. Too bad it won't let me resister my phone."}
{"Author": "Christian Muzzio", "Date": "August 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Awesome!  Very easy to install.  Instructions are detailed and easy to follow.  Pairing was simple enough however pairing my wife's phone required me to send her an ekey which wasn't explained.  Also setting up the app requires that you give it location permissions.  No problem with that but the app should ask during installation instead of having to change permissions in settings.  This is a must have for anyone.  I love the ekey sharing feature.  I can give someone temporary access or revoke anytime.  Very nice!"}
