{"Author": "William Giandoni", "Date": "May 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "This is a garbage system. I walked out of the house brushing the lock, activating then. Then I touched the lock again and it said the battery was low. I touched it a second time and was prompted to update to a newer version. I go to update and you have to remove the cover and hit the program button. Easy enough if you are in your house! I habe had this system for over a year and it is garbage. Spend your money on nest or something else."}
{"Author": "Lisa Faught", "Date": "May 16, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I paid alot of money for a door I have to use my key for anyway. At first I was having problems with it locking me out. But I fixed that by making sure I did not leave my phone within 50 feet of the door and I turned on the tap three times to lock. I think I would like this better if it was WiFi and could connect without having to purchase the additional bridge."}
{"Author": "Mary Miller", "Date": "March 22, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have this app installed on a Note 5 and a Pixel and they both have horrible bluetooth connectivity problems. I was so excited because the newest update allowed installation on my Pixel, and while I can lock/unlock within range, I can't update the lock. My Note 5 won't connect at all to lock/unlock or update. So so so frustrated that my $200+ lock isn't working as it's supposed to because of these app problems."}
{"Author": "Curtis DeBolt", "Date": "March 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app or website does not let a signed in user reset their security questions. Horribly slow support when I contacted them about it, they did not answer my question or resolve it but instead just asked why would someone want to do that. Also this is a security issue if you can't reset your security questions, and yet it's supposed to secure my house?   Cannot update my own security questions."}
{"Author": "diana f", "Date": "May 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My whole family enjoys the convenience of the Kevo 2nd gen and Kevo plus hub. I ran into issues trying to install the hub A: I am not the owner of the lock and B: the directions aren't very clear. We called customer service and they were extremely helpful and courteous. When the direction tell you to follow in app instructions. You must first push the + sign in the app to add the hub. No where and I repeat no where that I looked whether it was online or in forums did it say this. Since then we have had the hub hooked up for a week with no issues. We have been using the lock for 3 weeks. We did notice before the hub there was a little bit of a lag when locking or unlocking by Bluetooth but since it seems to be more efficient. The sending of ekeys is an excellent bonus we have used this option multiple times with no problems."}
{"Author": "L M", "Date": "March 15, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Terrible. I thought this would make my life easier. I hate that I have to have my Bluetooth on all the time. When I'm standing on my front to step searching for my phone then have to wait forever while it says 'searching, searching, searching...ERROR' I've never actually been able to use it the way it is supposed to work and always have to use my key. Just a $300 manual lock for my door."}
{"Author": "bob sarna", "Date": "May 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Ashley says it who t work with an Android. Ashley, it does. Another stated support it terrible. For various reasons I have called support. Might need to wait 5 or 10 minutes, but they were VERY friendly &amp; knowledgeable. I even emailed a couple questions and answers arrived in less than 48 hours. The locks work great, I swapped the batteries for the best i could find before installing the locks cause I'm smart...  Also, works great with Alexa (and add on unit). If you can Google, then there is no reason what so ever to say there are no I instructions or they are not clear.  The locks rock and so does their tech support."}
{"Author": "Ashley Davis", "Date": "March 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My Husband bought me a Kevo for Valentine's Day and it apparently is not compatible with Droid devices. This absolutely sucks! I was so excited. Now I can't even use it?! Droid phones are just as popular as iPhones these days!!"}
{"Author": "Raymond sump", "Date": "April 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Takes long time to unlock. More often than not after unlocking door (if it worked for that at the time) would send deadbolt lock out just after opening door. Lots of flaws"}
{"Author": "William Hagerty", "Date": "April 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Really what I hate the most is you can't disable users. You have to remove and add them back completely. It is slow but only like 5 secs at most."}
{"Author": "Kathy DeLorenzo-Macalone", "Date": "March 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I really want to LOVE this.  I love the concept but it's unreliable,  and if the battery on your phone goes too low then it's totally useless.  Also,  I want to be able to disable or limit times for some users but not delete them.  Can't seem to do that.  But when it works it's great"}
{"Author": "R a Z o R Jenkins", "Date": "March 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works great! Too bad my note 5 has weak blue tooth... my wife's LG phone works flawlessly... to those complaining about Bluetooth connectivity issues... I don't think it's so much the Kevo it's your device. Either way... great product cool lock!"}
{"Author": "Harold Rodriguez", "Date": "February 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The lock works whenever it wants even after doing the calibration. At times it will not open or close unless the phone is touching the bolt and that is pointless."}
{"Author": "jesse shaker", "Date": "May 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I bought the 1st gen kevo.  When installed I was prompted to do a update. Which kept failing.  Called kevo, they said it was the unit and they were going to send me a REFURB IN REPLACEMENT.  A REFURB!!!. This is because they are back ordered for 2 months. My unit was brand new.  I brought it back to best buy and exchanged and paid the difference on a 2nd gen kevo that has the same issue.  It will not update and the app is useless.  I have a samsung galaxy s6 edge, Bluetooth enabled with sharing.  Great idea poorly made.  Very disappointing. Will be returning...  also their customer service reps have very little information that helps. Sorry kevo I was very excited but you disappointed me."}
{"Author": "David Fisher", "Date": "March 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "For Kevo locks. Great idea. Great looking design. Terrible lock firmware and terrible support for this app. The locks really don't behave as advertised. To actually control or monitor the locks remotely, you have to buy the overpriced Kevo bridge that is never in stock. For this app, it took them in excess of 6 months to support Google Pixels. Didn't bother to replace the batteries in the Kevo. Planning to swap out the locks with Schlage ones this summer. Also updating all the door hardware in the house. Will not by Kwikset anything ever again."}
{"Author": "Justin Lentini", "Date": "March 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Still want to love this but can't. It randomly works even after following all the troubleshooting tips and suggestions. Everytime I get this to be \"somewhat\" reliable there's either a firmware or software update then it acts up again. I guess I'm the idiot for thinking this will work better after updates. Still doesn't work to this date and I've owned this terrible manual lock since they came out with 2.0 version several months ago."}
{"Author": "Kiesha Edge", "Date": "April 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Takes a long time to connect to my S7 Edge but connects to my husband's 7 Plus pretty quickly. Does not register if door is locked/unlocked by key or by hand so you won't see that in the history (my child still uses a key). Sometimes when it connects it won't unlock (got stuck outside once without a physical key and the Kevo wouldn't unlock, late to work that day)."}
{"Author": "Auhsten Buckallew", "Date": "February 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can't calibrate because the instructions are horrible. My phone set up on it to be the owner but hours later when trying to add a key the owner phone won't connect to it and the customer support is horrible and unclear. Horrible horrible horrible."}
{"Author": "Bryan Barnes", "Date": "April 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not compatible with new phones. LG G6 does not work. Good thing I haven't installed this yet. Probably will hang onto it for a week then send it back if problem isn't fixed. So glad I read the reviews first!"}
{"Author": "Chris Knorowski", "Date": "May 3, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Sometimes the bolt will pop out when the door isn't shut or while the door is closing causing it to hit the deadbolt hard. Deadbolt should be arter than that. Somewhat slow to react to touch. Should be a better way to share keys. Extra keys are not free."}
{"Author": "Mike Palmer", "Date": "March 20, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Constantly turns my Bluetooth off on my pixel. You never know it did it until you are driving around on the road and need to use your handsfree. At which point, you have to fumble around with everything trying to get Bluetooth enabled and connected to handsfree without causing a pileup on the freeway.  Just. leave. my. Bluetooth settings alone! Just use it, that's it Kevo!"}
{"Author": "Jean Alvarez", "Date": "March 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Kevo stopped working and it's infuriating. I hate standing outside my house for 10 minutes everyday until this stupid thing unlocks, sometimes it doesn't even unlock. It's pretty useless now."}
{"Author": "Scott B", "Date": "February 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "constantly having to take my phone out and then have to open the app to get my door to unlock. of I had known that, I would just fumble for my keys as it would be faster to get in my damn house. does not work consistently"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "April 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works great on our S7 and J7.  No issues at all.  Installation took about 45 minutes mostly because I didn't read the directions completely.   Could do it again in 20."}
{"Author": "Josh France", "Date": "April 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "My deadbolt needs an update all of a sudden and absolutely won't open till I do it.. I'm trapped outside now.. I guess I'm breaking into my own house now"}
{"Author": "Donna Tencza", "Date": "April 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I have a Samsung Note 5 and it works perfectly.  No issues at all.  Possibly all the negative comments are user error.  I also installed one for a friend and she loves hers also"}
{"Author": "kyle corn", "Date": "March 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Does not work woth my Samsung Galaxy S7 edge... does not pair and always asks for Bluetooth to be turned on when I try and update the app...."}
{"Author": "Carlos S", "Date": "March 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Phone bluetooth connection needs major improvements, battery life is very short, rechargable batteries highly recommended, the Kevo fob is worth every penny but defeats the purpose, Kevo Plus is awesome, highly encourage the investment, it's the best part of the Kevo setup without the Plus I would give it a 3 stars"}
{"Author": "James Coulombe", "Date": "May 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Don't waste your money.  App doesn't pair with lock, terrible instructions, terrible app and worst design imaginable."}
{"Author": "Kyle Verry", "Date": "May 14, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I like it. It has needed a bit of coaxing, but nothing beyond a reinstall of software on one phone and replacing batteries one time. Have a first gen (2+ years) and a second gen (1 year). My parents now have one too, and it was a set it, forget it. Mostly Nexus and Motorola products. The iPhone always needs the app open....good thing the parents have Nexus phones!!! ;)"}
{"Author": "Matt Brennan", "Date": "March 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Nice recent update. Still missing: history of manual lock/unlock, wildcard notifications (you have to set them up individually for every user/event combination), better nest integration (set nest home/away status instead of adjusting temp)"}
{"Author": "Leandro Escobar", "Date": "May 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app doesn't work on three different up to date devices and the physical lock and fobs are trash. Waste of $200."}
{"Author": "Christian Simpson", "Date": "April 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Email listed right here doesn't work * No Wink support * Notifications hard to set up and flaky * Android Wear often says No Locks"}
{"Author": "Mike Smith", "Date": "March 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It is awesome...I am not a person that's here to hype up the comments, but it works perfect with my ring doorbell. I just wished it worked the same so I could be able to unlock the door for my children if I am not home"}
{"Author": "Kevin Cheung", "Date": "March 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works alright for me. Takes a little while for the app to lock and unlock. But aside from the app, it easily locks &amp; unlocks with a simple touch on the deadbolt. I just turn on my Bluetooth as I'm approaching my door and voila!"}
{"Author": "Ramon Bruzos", "Date": "June 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 2 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Not compatible with some phones Says the phone is not compatible, app needs some work. I do love the lock."}
{"Author": "Stephanie Keith", "Date": "March 25, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Has to be restarted once in a while. When you're standing at the door with your arms full it is kind of annoying,  but everything else works great."}
{"Author": "Matthew Salvatore", "Date": "March 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Doesn't work with droid turbo. Lock only works with iPhone when app is open. Key fob doesn't always work. Eats through batteries on fob and on door. Highly recommend a different lock."}
{"Author": "Kenneth Gore", "Date": "May 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app has come a long way to echo others. Thx to the dev team. Keep up the good work! I would only ask for a way to backup the encryption keys so u dont have to reinitiate if something happens to your phone. At least the lock owner. Maybe only the owner actually;)"}
{"Author": "Elezar Kenig", "Date": "March 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I like the new app, wish there were more advanced notification options. Eg, I want it to always run in the background but I don't want a notification telling me about it. What if someone picks up my phone and sees that and now knows they can just get in?"}
{"Author": "Jerome Donovan", "Date": "February 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Doesn't work. Had been broken for many months with no sign of a fix. Depletes battery and can't uninstall"}
{"Author": "Chris Bowe", "Date": "April 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works well (for me). There are times I've had to reinstall the app to recalibrate the Bluetooth distance so it still works in my pocket. I've had this lock for around 2 years now and have NEVER used the physical key. Sometimes the lock is picky and flashes pink but I always take that as \"I recognize the device but didn't understand its location\" the devices way of not letting just anyone unlock your door with you inside."}
{"Author": "Mohammad Hassan", "Date": "April 23, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It runs in the background, if you think running your Bluetooth all the time is a hassle, then I suggest get rid of your iCrap and get an actual smartphone like a Samsung :)"}
{"Author": "Ryan Gordon", "Date": "April 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It's a bit slow sometimes but this is my only issue.  Very good app otherwise."}
{"Author": "Romeo Guishard Jr", "Date": "May 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It was awesome in the beginning. Seems like it's getting worse as thinner goes on. Seems like Bluetooth issues."}
{"Author": "Scott Lev", "Date": "April 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "1800 troubleshooting was quick enough.. lock and app seem flawless upon testing all features  Give it an 8 outta 10 .. maybe 2nd Gen is out and home depot still selling first at full price .. buy on amazon"}
{"Author": "michael cavallo", "Date": "May 13, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Does not perform well. The phone has to be in my hand, very close to the deadbolt, and still takes 2-3 tries.  Complete waste of time and money."}
{"Author": "Jennifer Lawson", "Date": "February 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Finally got all the kinks straightened out, thank goodness! 5 star app at last!"}
{"Author": "Nate Weibley", "Date": "February 26, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The 2.0 update and firmware update has made touch registration much faster. Also the accelerometer detection keeps the bolt from toggling accidentally while the door is moving now. New updates are overall great!"}
{"Author": "Tracie P.", "Date": "April 29, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "We have used Kevo for years and we will not go back to anything else!  Love the blue tooth capabilities and being able to send anyone a key.  So convenient!"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "May 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It refuses to pair with my phone.  And support seems to be unavailable.  Too aggravating for such an expensive device."}
{"Author": "Angel Perez", "Date": "March 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Love the ability to send ekeys for free now. I stopped carrying keys, with the exception of my car."}
{"Author": "Noella Soares", "Date": "March 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "The app works really well after the Nougat update."}
{"Author": "Adam Stadelmann", "Date": "April 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works great unless I have my phone in my back pocket.  Which is more a statement of the Bluetooth strength than the app or the lock.  We have it installed on 5 Nexus 5x's"}
{"Author": "Amanda Dormaier", "Date": "May 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "I love it I have a s5 Samsung and have no problem but if you get it read the instructions other wise wires get pinched and it does not work"}
{"Author": "Del Gaunt", "Date": "April 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It is so sensitive to touch if you bump it going outside it locks"}
{"Author": "", "Date": "March 9, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Kevo is great, I had the first gen and it worked for a while but the static shock you get when you rub feet on carpet screwed up the lock, now I am  using kevo convert with kevo plus and it works flawlessly"}
{"Author": "Julia Tucker", "Date": "May 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Front door done.  Work's so well we purchased a second one for the side door.  Next month will get one for the back door.  Love being able to cancel key's so easily too."}
{"Author": "Kenny Ng", "Date": "May 11, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "So many negative feedback.and u just ignore it.poor service.regret to get it.not recommended. I say again.not recommended!!!!!!"}
{"Author": "Tim \"TJ\" Jordan", "Date": "April 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "New update is awesome!  I can now remotely lock and unlock my front door from my bedroom or living room directly from the app.  Bluetooth connectivity is improved!"}
{"Author": "Jeremy Beamer", "Date": "March 19, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works every time. Great for when I am out running and don't have to carry a set of keys.  Friends can have access without adding another key to the keyring."}
{"Author": "Maurice Caviness", "Date": "April 1, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Working good so far....sometimes takes 2-3 tries to lock the door, but it does work. Only been using it for about 1 week at the time of this writing."}
{"Author": "Gus Sabogal", "Date": "April 18, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works great. Third Lock I install with no problems. Had an issue adding a virtual key, tech support was awesome. No problems with my Android devices. Never tested with iPhone."}
{"Author": "", "Date": "March 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Support for Pixel XL makes it 5 stars. \ud83d\ude00"}
{"Author": "Kuros M", "Date": "March 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Class action lawsuit. That's all I gotta say."}
{"Author": "Warren champ", "Date": "April 28, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Modern-day conveniences. This devices offers ability to share with friends and family, just one tap from your smartphone! \ud83d\udcf1"}
{"Author": "Dave Lindsay", "Date": "May 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Terrible lock, total junk, do not buy"}
{"Author": "Kim Rogich", "Date": "April 17, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Awful. Doesn't always open. Free keys don't work."}
{"Author": "Morgan Evans", "Date": "March 10, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Doesn't work on Google Pixel."}
{"Author": "Altyreek Swails", "Date": "March 5, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 3 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works when it wants to. Would be nice for wink, echo and google home integration"}
{"Author": "john edwards", "Date": "March 12, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "So far this is great. Was an easy installation and works really well, we'll see how it goes in the long-term."}
{"Author": "hillary fraser", "Date": "May 21, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "It still has issues with the Bluetooth losing signal at times, but overall a great app."}
{"Author": "Brian Groll", "Date": "March 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Asks for sign in every time app opens. Cannot use Bluetooth remote as I'm not logged in."}
{"Author": "Greg Lemon", "Date": "April 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "$200.00 Paperweight ! Takes WAY TOO LONG to locate and open the lock. Do yourself a BIG favour and Use a Key !!"}
{"Author": "Gary C", "Date": "February 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works on the lock most of the time. Sometimes it needs me to start up the app for the locking to work. Integrates very well with Nest."}
{"Author": "Daryl Hall", "Date": "February 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Good so far. Few days in but no problems yet. I will say easy to set up and install."}
{"Author": "Laurin Dunn", "Date": "March 4, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Does what it is supposed to do from time to time have Bluetooth issues, but works great for me."}
{"Author": "Tim Seward", "Date": "March 7, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Works fine on my Samsung note 5 and fairly easy to use.. however it's hard to find the calibration settings.."}
{"Author": "Nick Nock", "Date": "March 2, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "New update absolutely killed my battery. Go back or fix it please"}
{"Author": "Ridge Bandeen", "Date": "May 8, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 4 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Leaving the bluetooth on on my particular phone drains the battery, but used wisely it's a great app."}
{"Author": "Tamika Haynes", "Date": "April 24, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "So far so good.  Been using it for a week on both a Pixel and Galaxy S8 and it's working flawlessly."}
{"Author": "Linda Thomas", "Date": "February 27, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 5 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Easy to follow instructions and love not having to take my phone out yo unlock the door."}
{"Author": "Jesse Kaine", "Date": "May 6, 2017", "Stars": " Rated 1 stars out of five stars ", "Text": "Can't get pixel XL to pair at all, always says try again."}
